{"title_page": "McClain (band)", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2014}}\n{{Infobox musical artist|<!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject Musicians -->\n| name             = McClain\n| image            = McCLAIN band 2011 cropped.jpg\n| landscape        = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank -->\n| alt              = \n| caption          = McClain in 2011, from left to right: <br />Sierra McClain, [[China Anne McClain]], and Lauryn McClain\n| origin           = [[Atlanta, Georgia]], United States\n| Background       = group_or_band\n| alias            = {{flat list|\n* 3McClainGirls\n* McClain Sisters}}\n| genre            = {{flat list|\n* [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]\n* [[Pop music|pop]]}}\n| years_active     = 2005\u20132016 (on hiatus)\n| label            = [[Hollywood Records|Hollywood Records]] {{small|(2011\u201313)}}\n| website          = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} -->\n| current_members  = * [[China Anne McClain]]\n* Sierra McClain\n* Lauryn McClain\n}}\n'''McClain''' (formerly '''3McClainGirls''' and '''McClain Sisters''') is an American [[girl group]] that was formed in [[Atlanta, Georgia]] in 2004. The group consists of sisters [[China Anne McClain]], Sierra McClain, and Lauryn McClain. They signed with [[Hollywood Records]] in 2011 and released their debut single \"[[Go (McClain Sisters song)|Go]]\" in 2012. In 2013, the group left the record label. Their most recent single \"Feelin' Like\" was released in 2016. The group is now on hiatus and the sisters are pursuing their acting careers. \n\n== Early life ==\nSierra Aylina McClain was born on March 16, 1994<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/name/nm2057826/|title=Sierra Aylina McClain|website=IMDb|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>, Lauryn Alisa McClain was born on January 9, 1997<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/name/nm2055160/|title=Lauryn Alisa McClain|website=IMDb|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>, and China Anne McClain was born on August 25, 1998<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/name/nm1942207/|title=China Anne McClain|website=IMDb|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>. All three sisters were born and raised in [[Atlanta, Georgia]]. Sierra, Lauryn, and China grew up watching [[Disney]] films and musical classics, and come from an artistic and musical family<ref name=\"filmb\">{{cite web|url=http://www.filmbug.com/db/346128|title=Sierra, Lauryn & China Anne McClain|date=March 22, 2012|publisher=Filmbug.com}}</ref> Their father, Michael McClain, is a music producer who produced [[Solange Knowles]]' debut album. Their mother, Shontell McClain, is a songwriter and former screenwriter.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/name/nm2718277/|title=Shontell McClain|website=IMDb|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref> The sisters also have a little brother, Gabriel McClain, who was born on April 17, 2001<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/name/nm2532716/|title=Gabriel McClain|website=IMDb|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>.\n\nIn 2004, the sisters became interested in music when they watched their father write and produce songs. Soon after, the girls began to write songs, choreograph and dance.<ref name=\"lions\">{{cite web|url=http://www.lionsgatepublicity.com/epk/daddyslittlegirls/docs/pro_notes.doc|title=McClain notes on Lionsgate|date=March 22, 2012|publisher=lionsgatepublicity.com|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100206114300/http://lionsgatepublicity.com/epk/daddyslittlegirls/docs/pro_notes.doc|archivedate=February 6, 2010|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\n\n=== 2005\u20132011: 3McClainGirls and ''Daddy's Little Girls'' ===\nIn 2005, the sisters were discovered as actresses by a music executive who heard them sing and encouraged director [[Rob Hardy]] to audition China for his 2005 feature film ''[[The Gospel (film)|The Gospel]].'' China was cast as the character Alexis and her sisters were in the supporting cast.<ref name=\"dc\">{{cite web |url=http://disneychannelmedianet.com/web/showpage/showpage.aspx?program_id=900056&type=mcclain |title=Disney Channel Bio \u2013 China Anne McClain |publisher=Disney Channel Medianet |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/63XM5Q2Ie?url=http://disneychannelmedianet.com/web/showpage/showpage.aspx?program_id=900056&type=mcclain |archivedate=November 28, 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref> The sisters became more serious about a musical career and formed the girl group the 3McClainGirls. \n\nThey recorded their first song, \"Silly Games\". The song was produced by their father, Michael McClain, and written by their mother, Shontell McClain.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ovguide.com/3mcclaingirls-9202a8c04000641f8000000006afa58b# |title=3McClainGirls Music |publisher=OV Guide |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/63XM5Q2Ie?url=http://disneychannelmedianet.com/web/showpage/showpage.aspx?program_id=900056&type=mcclain |archivedate=November 28, 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref> In 2006 China joined the main cast of ''[[Tyler Perry's House of Payne]]'' as Jazmine Payne and Sierra made guest appearances. In 2007 the group starred in the film ''[[Daddy's Little Girls]]'' as the James sisters.<ref name=\"lions\" /> In 2008 the group recorded the song \"Daddy's Girls\",<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/daddys-girl-mw0001655815 |title=3mcclaingirls! Daddy's Girl |publisher=Allmusic |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/63XM5Q2Ie?url=http://disneychannelmedianet.com/web/showpage/showpage.aspx?program_id=900056&type=mcclain |archivedate=November 28, 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref> inspired by the movie, and released it exclusively on Myspace.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.myspace.com/mcclainsisters |title=3mcclaingirls Official Myspace |publisher=Myspace |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/63XM5Q2Ie?url=http://disneychannelmedianet.com/web/showpage/showpage.aspx?program_id=900056&type=mcclain |archivedate=November 28, 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref> In 2008 the group began posting videos on Youtube of themselves singing covers of songs and continued making acting appearances in films and on television.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCksYLtnxiIW0UTegpdbseMQ|title=3mcclaingirls|website=YouTube|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n\n=== 2011\u20132013: McClain Sisters, ''A.N.T. Farm'' and Hollywood Records ===\nOn June 14, 2011 the group signed with [[Hollywood Records]].<ref name=\"hollywoodrecords\">{{cite web|url=http://www.blackcelebkids.com/2012/03/13/mcclain-sisters-sign-with-hollywood-records/|title=MCCLAIN SISTERS SIGN WITH HOLLYWOOD RECORDS|publisher=Black Celeb Kids|date=June 14, 2011|access-date=February 9, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130126042852/http://www.blackcelebkids.com/2012/03/13/mcclain-sisters-sign-with-hollywood-records/|archive-date=January 26, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> The sisters originally planned to use the name III as their group name, the number representing the three McClain girls in the group, but that idea was scrapped.<ref name=\":1\" /> They instead changed their group name to the McClain Sisters. That same year China landed her own show on the [[Disney Channel]] called [[A.N.T. Farm]]. On October 11, 2011, the [[A.N.T. Farm (soundtrack)]] was released on which the group had two songs: \"Perfect Mistake\" and \"Electronic Apology\". The group had plans to release their debut album with the record label<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|last=Barnes|first=Brooks|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/05/11/arts/television/tween-stars-wanted-must-be-primed-for-pressure.html|title=Tween Stars Wanted: Must Be Primed for Pressure|date=2011-05-10|work=The New York Times|access-date=2020-04-05|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> but never did. In December the group performed their version of [[Jingle Bell Rock]] at the 2011 [[Disney Parks Christmas Day Parade]].<ref>{{Citation|title=Christmas Parade 2011 McClain Sisters - Celebrity Take with Jake|url=https://video.disney.com/watch/christmas-parade-2011-mcclain-sisters-4bb39f0d70be4a8833003b15|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tigerbeat.com/2011/11/exclusive-bop-and-tiger-beats-photo-shoot-with-china/onerepublic-and-china-anne-mcclain-and-the-mcclain-sisters-perform-for-the-2011-disney-parks-christmas-day-parade/|title=OneRepublic and China Anne McClain and The McClain Sisters Perform for The 2011 Disney Parks Christmas Day Parade {{!}} TigerBeat|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n\nOn March 4, 2012 they were the opening act in [[Houston]] for [[Big Time Rush (group)|Big Time Rush]] on their [[Better with U Tour]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.houstonchronicle.com/news/houston-texas/article/Big-Time-Rush-show-leaves-little-to-like-3381325.php|title=Big Time Rush show leaves little to like|date=2012-03-05|website=HoustonChronicle.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/houston-livestock-show-and-rodeo-officials-announce-star-studded-entertainer-lineup-ticket-sales-information-136945508.html|title=Houston Livestock Show and Rodeo\u2122 Officials Announce Star-studded Entertainer Lineup, Ticket Sales Information|last=Rodeo|first=Houston Livestock Show &|website=www.prnewswire.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref>  \n\nOn March 11, 2012 they performed a new song called \"Rise\" at the [[Mall of America]]. The song was written by the McClain Sisters and produced by father Michael McClain, and was the lead promotional single for the [[Disneynature]] film [[Chimpanzee (film)|''Chimpanzee'']]. The song was released on March 23, 2012. The music video premiered on March 25, 2012 during an episode of ''[[Austin & Ally]]''. It was also a featured song for [[Disney's Friends for Change]]..<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mallofamerica.com/upload/event/pdf/ChinaGuidelinesUPDATE.pdf|title=China Anne McClain & the McClain Sisters Performance and Signing|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> The music video later premiered online on March 26, 2012.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uxVeeqqAyf0|title=McClain Sisters - Rise (Official Video from Disneynature's Chimpanzee)|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> \n\nOn September 11, 2012, their single [[The Great Divide (McClain Sisters song)|The Great Divide]] was released which was featured in the Disney film [[Secret of the Wings]] and on the film's soundtrack [[Disney Fairies: Faith, Trust, and Pixie Dust]]. \n\nOn November 2, 2012, the McClain Sisters premiered their debut single \"[[Go (McClain Sisters song)|Go]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/go-single/id573043137|title=Music \u2013 Go - iTunes United States|publisher=iTunes Store (US). Apple|accessdate=September 26, 2012}}</ref> Lauryn and Sierra guest starred and performed the song, alongside China, on November 23, 2012 during the episode \"[[List of A.N.T. Farm episodes#ep41|chANTs of a lifetime]]\" for ''[[A.N.T. Farm]].'' \n\n=== 2013\u2013present: Leaving Hollywood Records, McClain, and hiatus ===\nIn December of 2013, China announced on Twitter that [[A.N.T. Farm]] would be ending after its third season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/chinamcclain/status/416460834571694080|title=It was GREAT filming ANT Farm but after 3 seasons it's come to an end. I'm excited about my secret projects and keeping you guys happy!|last=China\u2077|date=2013-12-26|website=@chinamcclain|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref> Shortly after this announcement, the McClain Sisters parted ways with [[Hollywood Records]]. After leaving the record label the group changed their name from the McClain Sisters to simply McClain. The group released an official lyric video for their single \"He Loves Me\" on YouTube on December 14, 2013.<ref>{{Citation|last=mcclainsisters|title=He Loves Me- Lyric Video|date=2013-12-14|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Z21wV7XRaqs|accessdate=2016-06-13}}</ref> The song then became available on iTunes on February 20, 2014. Later that year, McClain released a Christmas song called \"The Holiday Song\". \n\nThe last single the sisters released was \"Feelin' Like\" in 2016 and the group now seems to be on hiatus. All three sisters are pursuing their acting careers.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==Personal life==\nThey are [[Christians]] and reside in Los Angeles, California with their family.<ref>{{cite web|title=Biography of China |url=http://chinaanne.net/chinaanne/biography/ |work=chinaanne.net |accessdate=September 26, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121125013234/http://chinaanne.net/chinaanne/biography/ |archivedate=November 25, 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hollowverse.com/china-anne-mcclain/|title=China Anne McClain\u2019s Religion and Political Views|website=hollowverse.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n\n===Singles===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\" border=\"1\"\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:14em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Album\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"[[Disney's Friends for Change#Rise|Rise]]\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/rise-feat.-mcclain-sisters/id509693456|title=Rise \u2013 Single by McClain|publisher=iTunes Store (US). Apple|accessdate=September 26, 2012}}</ref>\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2012\n| rowspan=\"4\" {{n/a|Non-album singles}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"[[Go (McClain Sisters song)|Go]]\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"He Loves Me\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/he-loves-me-single/id827805733|title=He Loves Me \u2013 Single by McClain|publisher=iTunes Store (US). Apple|accessdate=September 26, 2012}}</ref>\n| 2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Feelin' Like\"<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=https://soundcloud.com/officialmcclain/feelin-like-ode-to-aaliyah|title=Feelin' Like \u2013 Single by McClain|publisher=Soundcloud|accessdate=January 14, 2020}}</ref>\n| 2016\n|-\n|}\n\n===Promotional singles===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\" border=\"1\"\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:14em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\"| Album\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Silly Games\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.youngblackstarz.org/2012/04/03/memory-lane-these-girls-had-no-time-for-silly-games/|title=MEMORY LANE: THESE GIRLS HAD NO TIME FOR \"SILLY GAMES\"|work=Young Black Stars|date= |accessdate=May 13, 2010}}</ref><br><span style=\"font-size:85%; <!--font-weight:normal;-->\">(featuring Tiff Mic)</span>\n| 2005\n| rowspan=\"2\" {{n/a|Non-album singles}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Daddy's Girl\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/daddys-girl/id275361079|title=3mcclaingirls! \u2013 Daddy's Girl|work=iTunes|date= |accessdate=May 13, 2010}}</ref>\n| 2008\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"[[Disney Fairies: Faith, Trust And Pixie Dust#The Great Divide|The Great Divide]]\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/great-divide-from-secret-wings/id556729644|title=The Great Divide \u2013 Single by McClain|publisher=iTunes Store (US). Apple|accessdate=September 26, 2012}}</ref>\n| 2012\n| ''[[Disney Fairies: Faith, Trust and Pixie Dust]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"The Holiday Song\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/the-holiday-song-single/id952382814|title=The Holiday Song - Single|publisher=iTunes Store (US). Apple|accessdate=September 26, 2012}}</ref>\n| 2014\n| {{n/a|Non-album single}}\n|-\n|}\n\n===Other appearances===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\" border=\"1\"\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:15em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\"| Album\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Perfect Mistake\"\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2011\n| rowspan=\"2\"| ''[[A.N.T. Farm (soundtrack)|A.N.T. Farm]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Electronic Apology\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Jingle Bell Rock]]\"\n| 2012\n| ''[[Disney Channel Holiday Playlist]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Sharp As a Razor\"\n| 2013\n| ''[[Shake It Up: I Love Dance|Shake It Up: I <3 Dance]]''\n|}\n\n===Music videos===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\" border=\"1\"\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:15em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\"| Year\n! cindy=\"sharp\"| Director\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"[[Rise (McClain Sisters song)|Rise]]\"\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2012\n| Mark Albert\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"The Great Divide\"\n| {{n/a}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==Concert tours==\n;Opening act:\n* 2012: [[Better with U Tour#Opening act|Better with U Tour]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blackcelebkids.com/2012/03/06/the-mcclain-sisters-take-to-the-stage/|title=THE MCCLAIN SISTERS TAKE TO THE STAGE|work=blackcelebkids.com|date=May 13, 2010|accessdate=May 13, 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120308123351/http://www.blackcelebkids.com/2012/03/06/the-mcclain-sisters-take-to-the-stage/|archive-date=March 8, 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref> {{small|([[Big Time Rush (band)|Big Time Rush]])}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://mcclainsistersmusic.com/ Official website]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Musical groups established in 2011]]\n[[Category:Sibling musical trios]]\n[[Category:American hip hop groups]]\n[[Category:American pop music groups]]\n[[Category:African-American girl groups]]\n[[Category:American contemporary R&B musical groups]]\n[[Category:American girl groups]]\n[[Category:Hollywood Records artists]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2014}}\n{{Infobox musical artist|<!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject Musicians -->\n| name             = McClain\n| image            = McCLAIN band 2011 cropped.jpg\n| landscape        = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank -->\n| alt              = \n| caption          = McClain in 2011, from left to right: <br />Sierra McClain, [[China Anne McClain]], and Lauryn McClain\n| origin           = [[Atlanta, Georgia]], United States\n| Background       = group_or_band\n| alias            = {{flat list|\n* 3McClainGirls\n* McClain Sisters}}\n| genre            = {{flat list|\n* [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]\n* [[Pop music|pop]]}}\n| years_active     = 2005\u20132016 (on hiatus)\n| label            = [[Hollywood Records|Hollywood Records]] {{small|(2011\u201313)}}\n| website          = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} -->\n| current_members  = * [[China Anne McClain]]\n* Sierra McClain\n* Lauryn McClain\n}}\n'''McClain''' (formerly '''3McClainGirls''' and '''McClain Sisters''') is an American [[girl group]] that was formed in [[Atlanta, Georgia]] in 2004. The group consists of sisters [[China Anne McClain]], Sierra McClain, and Lauryn McClain. They signed with [[Hollywood Records]] in 2011 and released their debut single \"[[Go (McClain Sisters song)|Go]]\" in 2012. In 2013, the group left the record label. Their most recent single \"Feelin' Like\" was released in 2016. The group is now on hiatus and the sisters are pursuing their acting careers. \n\n== Early life ==\nSierra Aylina McClain was born on March 16, 1994<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/name/nm2057826/|title=Sierra Aylina McClain|website=IMDb|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>, Lauryn Alisa McClain was born on January 9, 1997<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/name/nm2055160/|title=Lauryn Alisa McClain|website=IMDb|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>, and China Anne McClain was born on August 25, 1998<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/name/nm1942207/|title=China Anne McClain|website=IMDb|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>. All three sisters were born and raised in [[Atlanta, Georgia]]. Sierra, Lauryn, and China grew up watching [[Disney]] films and musical classics, and come from an artistic and musical family<ref name=\"filmb\">{{cite web|url=http://www.filmbug.com/db/346128|title=Sierra, Lauryn & China Anne McClain|date=March 22, 2012|publisher=Filmbug.com}}</ref> Their father, Michael McClain, is a music producer who produced [[Solange Knowles]]' debut album. Their mother, Shontell McClain, is a songwriter and former screenwriter.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/name/nm2718277/|title=Shontell McClain|website=IMDb|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref> The sisters also have a little brother, Gabriel McClain, who was born on April 17, 2001<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/name/nm2532716/|title=Gabriel McClain|website=IMDb|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>.\n\nIn 2004, the sisters became interested in music when they watched their father write and produce songs. Soon after, the girls began to write songs, choreograph and dance.<ref name=\"lions\">{{cite web|url=http://www.lionsgatepublicity.com/epk/daddyslittlegirls/docs/pro_notes.doc|title=McClain notes on Lionsgate|date=March 22, 2012|publisher=lionsgatepublicity.com|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100206114300/http://lionsgatepublicity.com/epk/daddyslittlegirls/docs/pro_notes.doc|archivedate=February 6, 2010|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\n\n=== 2005\u20132011: 3McClainGirls and ''Daddy's Little Girls'' ===\nIn 2005, the sisters were discovered as actresses by a music executive who heard them sing and encouraged director [[Rob Hardy]] to audition China for his 2005 feature film ''[[The Gospel (film)|The Gospel]].'' China was cast as the character Alexis and her sisters were in the supporting cast.<ref name=\"dc\">{{cite web |url=http://disneychannelmedianet.com/web/showpage/showpage.aspx?program_id=900056&type=mcclain |title=Disney Channel Bio \u2013 China Anne McClain |publisher=Disney Channel Medianet |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/63XM5Q2Ie?url=http://disneychannelmedianet.com/web/showpage/showpage.aspx?program_id=900056&type=mcclain |archivedate=November 28, 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref> The sisters became more serious about a musical career and formed the girl group the 3McClainGirls. \n\nThey recorded their first song, \"Silly Games\". The song was produced by their father, Michael McClain, and written by their mother, Shontell McClain.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ovguide.com/3mcclaingirls-9202a8c04000641f8000000006afa58b# |title=3McClainGirls Music |publisher=OV Guide |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/63XM5Q2Ie?url=http://disneychannelmedianet.com/web/showpage/showpage.aspx?program_id=900056&type=mcclain |archivedate=November 28, 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref> In 2006 China joined the main cast of ''[[Tyler Perry's House of Payne]]'' as Jazmine Payne and Sierra made guest appearances. In 2007 the group starred in the film ''[[Daddy's Little Girls]]'' as the James sisters.<ref name=\"lions\" /> In 2008 the group recorded the song \"Daddy's Girls\",<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/daddys-girl-mw0001655815 |title=3mcclaingirls! Daddy's Girl |publisher=Allmusic |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/63XM5Q2Ie?url=http://disneychannelmedianet.com/web/showpage/showpage.aspx?program_id=900056&type=mcclain |archivedate=November 28, 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref> inspired by the movie, and released it exclusively on Myspace.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.myspace.com/mcclainsisters |title=3mcclaingirls Official Myspace |publisher=Myspace |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/63XM5Q2Ie?url=http://disneychannelmedianet.com/web/showpage/showpage.aspx?program_id=900056&type=mcclain |archivedate=November 28, 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref> In 2008 the group began posting videos on Youtube of themselves singing covers of songs and continued making acting appearances in films and on television.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCksYLtnxiIW0UTegpdbseMQ|title=3mcclaingirls|website=YouTube|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n\n=== 2011\u20132013: McClain Sisters, ''A.N.T. Farm'' and Hollywood Records ===\nOn June 14, 2011 the group signed with [[Hollywood Records]].<ref name=\"hollywoodrecords\">{{cite web|url=http://www.blackcelebkids.com/2012/03/13/mcclain-sisters-sign-with-hollywood-records/|title=MCCLAIN SISTERS SIGN WITH HOLLYWOOD RECORDS|publisher=Black Celeb Kids|date=June 14, 2011|access-date=February 9, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130126042852/http://www.blackcelebkids.com/2012/03/13/mcclain-sisters-sign-with-hollywood-records/|archive-date=January 26, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> The sisters originally planned to use the name III as their group name, the number representing the three McClain girls in the group, but that idea was scrapped.<ref name=\":1\" /> They instead changed their group name to the McClain Sisters. That same year China landed her own show on the [[Disney Channel]] called [[A.N.T. Farm]]. On October 11, 2011, the [[A.N.T. Farm (soundtrack)]] was released on which the group had two songs: \"Perfect Mistake\" and \"Electronic Apology\". The group had plans to release their debut album with the record label<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|last=Barnes|first=Brooks|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/05/11/arts/television/tween-stars-wanted-must-be-primed-for-pressure.html|title=Tween Stars Wanted: Must Be Primed for Pressure|date=2011-05-10|work=The New York Times|access-date=2020-04-05|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> but never did. In December the group performed their version of [[Jingle Bell Rock]] at the 2011 [[Disney Parks Christmas Day Parade]].<ref>{{Citation|title=Christmas Parade 2011 McClain Sisters - Celebrity Take with Jake|url=https://video.disney.com/watch/christmas-parade-2011-mcclain-sisters-4bb39f0d70be4a8833003b15|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tigerbeat.com/2011/11/exclusive-bop-and-tiger-beats-photo-shoot-with-china/onerepublic-and-china-anne-mcclain-and-the-mcclain-sisters-perform-for-the-2011-disney-parks-christmas-day-parade/|title=OneRepublic and China Anne McClain and The McClain Sisters Perform for The 2011 Disney Parks Christmas Day Parade {{!}} TigerBeat|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n\nOn March 4, 2012 they were the opening act in [[Houston]] for [[Big Time Rush (group)|Big Time Rush]] on their [[Better with U Tour]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.houstonchronicle.com/news/houston-texas/article/Big-Time-Rush-show-leaves-little-to-like-3381325.php|title=Big Time Rush show leaves little to like|date=2012-03-05|website=HoustonChronicle.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/houston-livestock-show-and-rodeo-officials-announce-star-studded-entertainer-lineup-ticket-sales-information-136945508.html|title=Houston Livestock Show and Rodeo\u2122 Officials Announce Star-studded Entertainer Lineup, Ticket Sales Information|last=Rodeo|first=Houston Livestock Show &|website=www.prnewswire.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref>  \n\nOn March 11, 2012 they performed a new song called \"Rise\" at the [[Mall of America]].The song was written by the McClain Sisters and produced by father Michael McClain, and was the lead promotional single for the [[Disneynature]] film [[Chimpanzee (film)|''Chimpanzee'']]. The song was released on March 23, 2012. The music video premiered on March 25, 2012 during an episode of ''[[Austin & Ally]]''. It was also a featured song for [[Disney's Friends for Change]]..<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mallofamerica.com/upload/event/pdf/ChinaGuidelinesUPDATE.pdf|title=China Anne McClain & the McClain Sisters Performance and Signing|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> The music video later premiered online on March 26, 2012.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uxVeeqqAyf0|title=McClain Sisters - Rise (Official Video from Disneynature's Chimpanzee)|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> \n\nOn September 11, 2012, their single [[The Great Divide (McClain Sisters song)|The Great Divide]] was released which was featured in the Disney film [[Secret of the Wings]] and on the film's soundtrack [[Disney Fairies: Faith, Trust, and Pixie Dust]]. \n\nOn November 2, 2012, the McClain Sisters premiered their debut single \"[[Go (McClain Sisters song)|Go]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/go-single/id573043137|title=Music \u2013 Go - iTunes United States|publisher=iTunes Store (US). Apple|accessdate=September 26, 2012}}</ref> Lauryn and Sierra guest starred and performed the song, alongside China, on November 23, 2012 during the episode \"[[List of A.N.T. Farm episodes#ep41|chANTs of a lifetime]]\" for ''[[A.N.T. Farm]].'' \n\n=== 2013\u2013present: Leaving Hollywood Records, McClain, and hiatus ===\nIn December of 2013, China announced on Twitter that [[A.N.T. Farm]] would be ending after its third season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/chinamcclain/status/416460834571694080|title=It was GREAT filming ANT Farm but after 3 seasons it's come to an end. I'm excited about my secret projects and keeping you guys happy!|last=China\u2077|date=2013-12-26|website=@chinamcclain|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref> Shortly after this announcement, the McClain Sisters parted ways with [[Hollywood Records]]. After leaving the record label the group changed their name from the McClain Sisters to simply McClain. The group released an official lyric video for their single \"He Loves Me\" on YouTube on December 14, 2013.<ref>{{Citation|last=mcclainsisters|title=He Loves Me- Lyric Video|date=2013-12-14|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Z21wV7XRaqs|accessdate=2016-06-13}}</ref> The song then became available on iTunes on February 20, 2014. Later that year, McClain released a Christmas song called \"The Holiday Song\". \n\nThe last single the sisters released was \"Feelin' Like\" in 2016 and the group now seems to be on hiatus. All three sisters are pursuing their acting careers.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==Personal life==\nThey are [[Christians]] and reside in Los Angeles, California with their family.<ref>{{cite web|title=Biography of China |url=http://chinaanne.net/chinaanne/biography/ |work=chinaanne.net |accessdate=September 26, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121125013234/http://chinaanne.net/chinaanne/biography/ |archivedate=November 25, 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hollowverse.com/china-anne-mcclain/|title=China Anne McClain\u2019s Religion and Political Views|website=hollowverse.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n\n===Singles===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\" border=\"1\"\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:14em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Album\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"[[Disney's Friends for Change#Rise|Rise]]\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/rise-feat.-mcclain-sisters/id509693456|title=Rise \u2013 Single by McClain|publisher=iTunes Store (US). Apple|accessdate=September 26, 2012}}</ref>\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2012\n| rowspan=\"4\" {{n/a|Non-album singles}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"[[Go (McClain Sisters song)|Go]]\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"He Loves Me\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/he-loves-me-single/id827805733|title=He Loves Me \u2013 Single by McClain|publisher=iTunes Store (US). Apple|accessdate=September 26, 2012}}</ref>\n| 2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Feelin' Like\"<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=https://soundcloud.com/officialmcclain/feelin-like-ode-to-aaliyah|title=Feelin' Like \u2013 Single by McClain|publisher=Soundcloud|accessdate=January 14, 2020}}</ref>\n| 2016\n|-\n|}\n\n===Promotional singles===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\" border=\"1\"\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:14em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\"| Album\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Silly Games\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.youngblackstarz.org/2012/04/03/memory-lane-these-girls-had-no-time-for-silly-games/|title=MEMORY LANE: THESE GIRLS HAD NO TIME FOR \"SILLY GAMES\"|work=Young Black Stars|date= |accessdate=May 13, 2010}}</ref><br><span style=\"font-size:85%; <!--font-weight:normal;-->\">(featuring Tiff Mic)</span>\n| 2005\n| rowspan=\"2\" {{n/a|Non-album singles}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Daddy's Girl\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/daddys-girl/id275361079|title=3mcclaingirls! \u2013 Daddy's Girl|work=iTunes|date= |accessdate=May 13, 2010}}</ref>\n| 2008\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"[[Disney Fairies: Faith, Trust And Pixie Dust#The Great Divide|The Great Divide]]\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/great-divide-from-secret-wings/id556729644|title=The Great Divide \u2013 Single by McClain|publisher=iTunes Store (US). Apple|accessdate=September 26, 2012}}</ref>\n| 2012\n| ''[[Disney Fairies: Faith, Trust and Pixie Dust]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"The Holiday Song\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/the-holiday-song-single/id952382814|title=The Holiday Song - Single|publisher=iTunes Store (US). Apple|accessdate=September 26, 2012}}</ref>\n| 2014\n| {{n/a|Non-album single}}\n|-\n|}\n\n===Other appearances===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\" border=\"1\"\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:15em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\"| Album\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Perfect Mistake\"\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2011\n| rowspan=\"2\"| ''[[A.N.T. Farm (soundtrack)|A.N.T. Farm]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Electronic Apology\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Jingle Bell Rock]]\"\n| 2012\n| ''[[Disney Channel Holiday Playlist]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Sharp As a Razor\"\n| 2013\n| ''[[Shake It Up: I Love Dance|Shake It Up: I <3 Dance]]''\n|}\n\n===Music videos===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\" border=\"1\"\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:15em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\"| Year\n! cindy=\"sharp\"| Director\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"[[Rise (McClain Sisters song)|Rise]]\"\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2012\n| Mark Albert\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"The Great Divide\"\n| {{n/a}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==Concert tours==\n;Opening act:\n* 2012: [[Better with U Tour#Opening act|Better with U Tour]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blackcelebkids.com/2012/03/06/the-mcclain-sisters-take-to-the-stage/|title=THE MCCLAIN SISTERS TAKE TO THE STAGE|work=blackcelebkids.com|date=May 13, 2010|accessdate=May 13, 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120308123351/http://www.blackcelebkids.com/2012/03/06/the-mcclain-sisters-take-to-the-stage/|archive-date=March 8, 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref> {{small|([[Big Time Rush (band)|Big Time Rush]])}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://mcclainsistersmusic.com/ Official website]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Musical groups established in 2011]]\n[[Category:Sibling musical trios]]\n[[Category:American hip hop groups]]\n[[Category:American pop music groups]]\n[[Category:African-American girl groups]]\n[[Category:American contemporary R&B musical groups]]\n[[Category:American girl groups]]\n[[Category:Hollywood Records artists]]\n", "name_user": "Factfanatic1", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200e2011\u20132013: McClain Sisters, A.N.T. Farm and Hollywood Records", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/McClain_(band)"}
{"title_page": "Perry Farrell", "text_new": "{{short description|American singer-songwriter and musician|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=July 2014}}\n{{Infobox musical artist  <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject Musicians -->\n| name                = Perry Farrell\n| image               = Perry Farrell performing with Jane's Addiction at BFD 2012.jpg\n| caption             = Perry Farrell performing with Jane's Addiction at BFD 2012\n| image_size          = 220px\n| background          = solo_singer\n| birth_name          = Peretz Bernstein\n| alias               = DJ Peretz\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1959|3|29}}\n| birth_place         = [[Queens]], [[New York City]], [[New York (state)|New York]], U.S.\n| instrument          = {{flatlist|\n*[[Vocals]]\n*[[turntables]]\n}}<!-- Only primary instruments. -->\n| genre               = {{flatlist|\n*[[Alternative rock]]<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.allmusic.com/artist/perry-farrell-mn0000312991/biography | title=Perry Farrell biography | publisher=[[Allmusic]] | accessdate=November 8, 2015 | author=Prato, Greg}}</ref>\n*[[hard rock]]<ref>{{cite web | url=http://exclaim.ca/music/article/perry_farrell-rev | title=Perry Farrell - Rev | work=[[Exclaim!]] | date=December 1, 1999 | accessdate=December 19, 2015 | author=Gramlich, Chris}}</ref>\n*[[electronica]]<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/song-yet-to-be-sung-mw0000004554 | title=Perry Farrell - Song Yet to Be Sung | publisher=[[Allmusic]] | accessdate=November 8, 2015 | author=[[Stephen Thomas Erlewine|Erlewine, Stephen Thomas]]}}</ref>\n}}\n| occupation          = {{flatlist|\n*Singer-songwriter\n*musician\n*DJ\n}}\n| years_active        = 1981\u2013present\n| label               = {{flatlist|\n*[[Warner Bros. Records|Warner Bros.]]\n*[[EMI]]/[[Capitol Records|Capitol]]\n*[[Columbia Records|Columbia]]\n}}\n| associated_acts     = {{flatlist|\n*[[Jane's Addiction]]\n*[[Porno for Pyros]]\n*[[Psi Com]]\n*[[Satellite Party]]\n*PerryEtty vs [[Chris Cox (DJ)|Chris Cox]]\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Perry Farrell''' (born '''Peretz Bernstein'''; March 29, 1959)<ref name=biography/><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.papermag.com/kabalapalooza-perry-farrell-1425145754.html | title=Kabalapalooza: Perry Farrell | work=[[Paper (magazine)|Paper]] | date=February 1, 2001 | accessdate=November 8, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://nypost.com/2011/10/16/surf-drugs-and-rock-n-roll/ | title=Surf, drugs and rock \u2019n\u2019 roll | work=[[New York Post]] | date=October 16, 2011 | accessdate=November 8, 2015 | author=Aquilante, Dan}}</ref> is an American singer-songwriter and musician, best known as the frontman for the [[alternative rock]] band [[Jane's Addiction]]. Farrell created the touring festival [[Lollapalooza]] as a farewell tour for Jane's Addiction in 1991; it has since evolved into an annual destination festival. Farrell continues to produce Lollapalooza with partners William Morris Agency and C3 Presents. Farrell has also led the alternative rock groups [[Porno for Pyros]] and [[Satellite Party]]. He is the only person who has performed at all twelve [[Coachella Valley Music and Arts Festival]]s to date, having appeared under five different names (Perry Farrell, Jane's Addiction, DJ Peretz, Satellite Party, and PuppiesDUH).\n\n==Biography==\nBorn as Peretz Bernstein in [[Queens]], [[New York City]], [[New York (state)|New York]], he spent his grade-school years in [[Woodmere, New York|Woodmere, Long Island]], and moved to [[North Miami Beach]], [[Florida]], with his [[Jewish]] family during his teens.<ref name=biography>Mullen, Brendan. [https://books.google.com/books?id=RXE0biSWhGIC&pg=PA1&lpg=PA1&dq=Perry+Farrell+woodmere&source=bl&ots=YLqsov-p7W&sig=xmSelAtE7cA0gzjbGznpMFAMOJI&hl=en&ei=MBjMSrfsLYSQsgOrqdCPAQ&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1#v=onepage&q=Perry%20Farrell%20woodmere&f=false Google Books], ''Whores: An Oral Biography of Perry Farrell and Jane's Addiction''. Cambridge: Da Capo, 2005. {{ISBN|0-306-81347-5}}</ref> His father was a jeweler and his mother was an artist who died by suicide when Farrell was three, an event later noted in the Jane's Addiction songs \"Then She Did\" and \"Twisted Tales\". \n\nHis early musical influences included [[The Beatles]], [[The Rolling Stones]], [[Led Zeppelin]], [[Sly & The Family Stone]] and [[James Brown]].<ref name=biography/> Soon after, he discovered [[David Bowie]], [[Iggy Pop]] and [[Lou Reed]]. Following graduation from high school, Farrell moved to California in the early 1980s to live as a surfer.  There, he lived in his car and made money working construction and waiting tables.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.spin.com/2003/07/my-life-music-perry-farrell/|title=My Life in Music: Perry Farrell|publisher=Spin.com|accessdate=2013-07-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kevchino.com/band/perry-farrell/1149|title=Perry Farrell|publisher=Kevchino.com|accessdate=2013-07-13|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141226132825/http://kevchino.com/band/perry-farrell/1149|archivedate=December 26, 2014|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nHe has a son, Yobel, with ex-girlfriend Christine Cagle.<ref>{{cite web|author=Ben Mitchell |url=https://www.theguardian.com/theobserver/2003/aug/03/features.magazine57 |title=The story of Jane's Addiction &#124; From the Observer |publisher=The Guardian |date= |accessdate=2017-08-10}}</ref> In 2002, Farrell married [[Etty Lau Farrell]], a professional dancer and singer who has performed in all the Jane's Addiction shows since the 1997 Relapse tour.  The couple now have two sons together, Hezron Wolfgang and Izzadore Bravo.\n\n==Music career==\n\n===Psi Com (1981\u20131985)===\nHe became the frontman for the [[Post-punk]] band [[Psi Com]] in Los Angeles, and traveled in a larger community of area musicians including the bands [[X (U.S. band)|X]], [[Red Hot Chili Peppers]], [[Fishbone]], and [[The Minutemen (band)|Minutemen]].  Psi Com broke up around 1985 and Farrell met [[Eric Avery]] through mutual friends. The two began jam sessions which would become the initial foundation for Jane's Addiction. It was during this period that Bernstein chose the pseudonym Perry Farrell for himself as a play on the word \"peripheral\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/music/artist/farrell_perry/artist.jhtml|title=Perry Farrell &#124; New Music And Songs|publisher=MTV|date=March 29, 1959|accessdate=2013-07-13}}</ref>\n\n===Jane's Addiction <small>(1985\u20131991, 1997, 2001\u20132004, 2008\u2013present)</small>===\nJane's Addiction made its name in mid-1980s LA by building up a rabid fan base with legendary, high-energy shows in small LA rock clubs. Jane's Addiction, prior to their first break-up, released three albums ''[[Jane's Addiction (album)|Jane's Addiction]]'', ''[[Nothing's Shocking]]'' and ''[[Ritual de lo Habitual]]''. A B-sides album from the ''Ritual'' sessions, titled ''Live and Rare'' was released in Japan. Late in 1991, Jane's Addiction broke up due to internal tensions over differing ideologies mostly centering on drug use, notably Farrell's severe addiction to heroin. Around this time, as mentioned in the SPIN Magazine (1991 Vol. 7 Num. 3) article about their \"Ritual\" tour, a rumor got around that Farrell had contracted HIV. Apparently for amusement, Farrell would tease audiences with \"news\" of his supposed health and would neither confirm nor deny its truth. \nIn 1993 Farrell and his ex-girlfriend Casey Niccoli released a film called ''[[Gift (1993 film)|Gift]]'' that featured Jane's Addiction. Gift was released by [[Warner Brothers]]. In 1997, Jane's Addiction reformed for a brief reunion tour with [[Flea (musician)|Flea]] replacing Avery on bass. The \"Relapse Tour\" was supported with the release of ''[[Kettle Whistle (album)|Kettle Whistle]]'', a rarities album featuring four new songs. {{citation needed|date=February 2014}}\n\nFarrell has sometimes been credited with changing the fortunes of the [[Coachella Valley Music and Arts Festival]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://musicians.about.com/od/musicfestivals/p/coachella.htm|title=Coachella Music Festival \u2013 Coachella \u2013 Profile of Coachella Music Festival|publisher=Musicians.about.com|date=June 22, 2013|accessdate=2013-07-13}}</ref> Following the festival's disastrous first year in 1999, the event was not held in 2000. In 2001, a decision was made to organize the festival again, but just a few months before the festival was set to occur, there was still no headlining group. Farrell, who was friends with the festival's organizers, decided to reunite Jane's Addiction for the 2001 event, which helped draw large crowds and allowed the festival to yield a profit (which was not the case in 1999). This began a Coachella tradition of reuniting at least one major artist each year.\n\nFarrell again toured with Jane's Addiction in 2001 and 2003.  In 2003, Jane's Addiction released an album, ''[[Strays (Jane's Addiction album)|Strays]]''. It quickly became one of their best selling records and was certified gold in the USA and silver in UK.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.riaa.com/goldandplatinumdata.php?table=SEARCH_RESULTS |title=Gold & Platinum Searchable Database \u2013 July 12, 2013 |publisher=RIAA |accessdate=2013-07-13 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070626051113/http://www.riaa.com/goldandplatinumdata.php?table=SEARCH_RESULTS |archivedate=June 26, 2007 |df=mdy-all }}</ref><ref>[http://www.bpi.co.uk/platinum/platinumright.asp?rq=search_plat&r_id=31076] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090218103035/http://www.bpi.co.uk/platinum/platinumright.asp?rq=search_plat&r_id=31076|date=February 18, 2009}}</ref> They toured extensively in North America and Europe, brought back [[Lollapalooza]] for the first time since 1997, as well as performing at the [[Big Day Out]] festivals in Australia and [[New Zealand]]. Internal struggles saw the band split up again in early 2004. A \"best of\" release following the breakup of this incarnation of the band was released in 2006, titled ''[[Up from the Catacombs - The Best of Jane's Addiction|Up from the Catacombs]]''.\n\nThe four original members of Jane's Addiction played their first show together in 17 years at the first United States edition of the NME Awards on April 23, 2008, and played two small shows in Los Angeles during Winter 2008. The band is the first American band to receive the \"God Like Genius\" Award. The reunited Jane's Addiction re-debuted at [[SXSW]] in 2009 and kicked off a summer tour with [[Nine Inch Nails]]. Eric Avery again left the band in late 2009, leaving Farrell, Navarro and Perkins as the remaining members of Jane's Addiction. The band with [[Dave Sitek]] on bass released ''[[The Great Escape Artist]]'' in 2011 and have continued to tour.\n\n===Porno for Pyros (1992\u20131998)===\n\nFollowing the break-up of Jane's Addiction, Farrell formed [[Porno for Pyros]] with former bandmate [[Stephen Perkins]] as well as newcomers [[Peter DiStefano]] on guitar and [[Martyn LeNoble]] on bass. Together they released two albums, ''[[Porno for Pyros (album)|Porno for Pyros]]'' and ''[[Good God's Urge]]''.\n\n===Solo career (1999\u2013present)===\n[[File:PerryFarrell.jpg|thumb|220px|right|Perry Farrell with Jane's Addiction <br />December 3, 2009]]\n\nKicking off his solo career, Farrell released ''[[Rev (Perry Farrell album)|rev]]'' in 1999, a compilation featuring songs from his previous two bands as well as two new solo songs. In 2001, he released his debut solo album, ''[[Song Yet to Be Sung]]'', whose lyrics are inspired by [[Kabballah]].\n\nFarrell has released a number of solo tracks online, all of them recorded with the involvement of wife Etty Lau. Their song \"Go All the Way (Into the Twilight)\" appeared on the ''[[Twilight (2008 film)|Twilight]]'' film soundtrack.<ref>[http://www.theinsider.com/photos/1324248_Twilight_Soundtrack_s_Number_1_And_The_Movie_Isn_t_Out] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081114132423/http://www.theinsider.com/photos/1324248_Twilight_Soundtrack_s_Number_1_And_The_Movie_Isn_t_Out|date=November 14, 2008}}</ref>\n\nIn October 2018, Farrell signed with [[BMG Rights Management]], which will release his upcoming album ''Kind Heaven'' in 2019.<ref name=\"kind\">{{cite web |title=JANE'S ADDICTION Frontman PERRY FARRELL Signs With BMG For New Solo Album, 'Kind Heaven' |url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/janes-addiction-frontman-perry-farrell-signs-with-bmg-for-new-solo-album-kind-heaven |website=[[Blabbermouth.net]] |accessdate=March 29, 2019 |date=October 16, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Satellite Party (2004\u20132008)===\n[[File:PerryFarrellJune07.jpg|thumb|right|200px|Farrell performing at the London Astoria in June 2007]]\nFarrell formed a new band/theatrical entity entitled [[The Satellite Party]]. Satellite Party is a concept album and is the story of a fictional band of musicians called ''The Solutionists'' who are trying to change the world.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.monstersandcritics.com/music/news/article_1255829.php/Farrell_s_Satellite_Party_announces_online_premiere_of_Wish_Upon_A_Dog_Star |title=Farrell's Satellite Party announces online premiere of 'Wish Upon A Dog Star' |publisher=Monsters and Critics |date=February 5, 2007 |accessdate=2013-07-13 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714122803/http://www.monstersandcritics.com/music/news/article_1255829.php/Farrell_s_Satellite_Party_announces_online_premiere_of_Wish_Upon_A_Dog_Star |archivedate=July 14, 2014 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> Farrell conceived the project with his wife [[Etty Lau Farrell]].  Etty sings and plays her part on the record as well as the live stage shows. Satellite Party made its debut in Los Angeles at The Key Club on July 18, 2005, followed by a performance at Lollapalooza 2005, held in [[Grant Park (Chicago)|Grant Park]] in downtown Chicago on July 24, 2005.\n\nTheir debut album, ''[[Ultra Payloaded]]'', was released on May 29, 2007, on [[Columbia Records]], with contributions from artists such as [[John Frusciante]] and [[Flea (musician)|Flea]] of the [[Red Hot Chili Peppers]], electronic dance producers [[Hybrid (Welsh band)|Hybrid]], former [[Red Hot Chili Peppers]]/[[Pearl Jam]] drummer [[Jack Irons]], [[Joy Division]]/[[New Order (band)|New Order]] bassist [[Peter Hook]], and [[Fergie (singer)|Fergie]] of [[The Black Eyed Peas]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Harris |first=Chris |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1501007/flea-contributing-new-farrell-project.jhtml |title=Flea, Frusciante Contributing To Farrell's Next Big Concept \u2013 Music, Celebrity, Artist News |publisher=MTV.com |date=April 29, 2005 |accessdate=2013-07-13}}</ref>\n\nSatellite Party performed at the [[Coachella Valley Music and Arts Festival]] on April 27, 2007. On June 8 they performed at the [[Download Festival]] at Donington, UK.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.downloadfestival.co.uk/history/2007 |title=DOWNLOAD FESTIVAL 2007 &#124; Download Festival 2013 |publisher=Downloadfestival.co.uk |date= |accessdate=2013-07-13}}</ref> On June 29 they performed alongside [[Pearl Jam]], [[Kings of Leon]] and [[Queens of the Stone Age]] at [[Rock Werchter]], Belgium. They performed at Buzz Beach Ball 3 in [[Kansas City, Missouri|Kansas City]], Missouri (a concert sponsored by [[KRBZ]]), and EndFest 16 in [[Seattle, Washington]].\n\n==Lollapalooza==\nIn 1991, prior to Jane's Addiction dissolving, Farrell, Ted Gardener, and Marc Geiger created the [[Lollapalooza]] festival as a farewell tour for Jane's Addiction. From its inception through 1997, and its revival in 2003, the festival toured North America. In 2004, the festival organizers decided to expand the dates to two days per city, but poor ticket sales forced the tour to be canceled.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/life/music/news/2004-06-22-festival-canceled_x.htm |title=Lollapalooza 2004 cancels all dates |publisher=Usatoday.Com |date=June 22, 2004 |accessdate=2013-07-13}}</ref> In 2005, Farrell and the [[William Morris Agency]] partnered up with [[Austin, Texas]]-based company Capital Sports Entertainment (now [[C3 Presents]]) and retooled it as a weekend destination festival in [[Grant Park (Chicago)|Grant Park]], Chicago, Illinois.\n\n===Kidzapalooza===\nIn 2005, music producer [[Tor Hyams]] approached Farrell with the idea of creating a kids' stage with family-friendly fare at [[Lollapalooza]].  Kidzapalooza came to be that year, produced by Hyams and continues to this day with guests like [[Slash (musician)|Slash]], [[Patti Smith]] and [[LeAnn Rimes]] appearing in the lineup of artists.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kidzapalooza.com/about/ |title=Kidzapalooza |publisher=Kidzapalooza |date= |accessdate=2013-07-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.timeoutchicagokids.com/arts-entertainment/movies-music-stage/42415/kidzapalooza-2011 |title=Kidzapalooza 2011 lineup announced |publisher=Time Out Chicago Kids |date=May 10, 2011 |accessdate=2013-07-13}}</ref>\n\n===PurimPalooza 2006===\nIn 2006, Farrell performed at Purimpalooza, which celebrates the Jewish holiday of [[Purim]]. It was a concert for all ages and presented different Jewish musical groups. It took place in [[Ruby Skye]] in San Francisco, and featured bands including Moshav, Chutzpah, and [[Matisyahu]].\n\n==Work outside music==\nFarrell has also made a docudrama titled ''Gift'' released in 1993 which featured various songs by Farrell and included Farrell's then-girlfriend Casey Niccoli. [[Gift (1993 film)|Gift]] was released to VHS home video by Warner Bros but never released to DVD.\n\nHe joined forces with [[Tom Morello]] and his [[Axis of Justice]] tour to raise money for the homeless in Los Angeles and together they both physically removed debris in the [[Ninth Ward]] of New Orleans in the aftermath of Hurricane Katrina to assist local musicians.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thenation.com/article/relentless-activism-tom-morello |title=The Relentless Activism of Tom Morello |first=Z.P. |last=Heller |publisher=The Nation |date=September 15, 2008 |accessdate=2013-07-13}}</ref> They also fund-raised for \"Road Recovery\" a New York non-profit organization which helps young people battling with addiction and other adversities.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.roadrecovery.org |title=Home |publisher=Road Recovery |date= |accessdate=2013-07-13}}</ref>\n\nFarrell is an environmentalist. He met with British prime minister [[Tony Blair]] at [[10 Downing Street]] on January 31, 2007, to discuss global warming. He presented Blair with a CD of the Satellite Party track \"Woman in the Window\".\n\nHe worked with [[Global Cool]] in 2007 to help promote green living.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nme.com/news/perry-farrell/26148 |title=Perry Farrell, Doors drummer launch Global Cool &#124; News |publisher=Nme.Com |date=January 30, 2007 |accessdate=2013-07-13}}</ref>\n\nFarrell has worked to bring music festivals to Israel, including Lollapalooza, and Jane's Addiction itself has performed in Israel.<ref name=\"spin.com\">{{cite web|url=https://www.spin.com/2012/08/perry-farrell-will-bring-lollapalooza-2013-israel/ |title=Perry Farrell Will Bring Lollapalooza 2013 to Israel |publisher=SPIN |date=2012-08-06 |accessdate=2017-08-10}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Billboard |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/1521648/lollapalooza-israel-canceled-were-sorry |title=Lollapalooza Israel Canceled: 'We're Sorry' |publisher=Billboard |date=2013-01-23 |accessdate=2017-08-10}}</ref> However, the Lollapalooza event fell through, with the organizers citing financial concerns and lack of talent willing to perform in Israel. Farrell starred and sang at a \"Stand with Israel\" party held at 7 World Trade Center, just outside [[Ground Zero]] in New York City.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/all_comments?v=sAmQE98wN3Q |title=Perry Farrell at Stand with Israel Event in NYC |publisher=YouTube |date= |accessdate=2017-08-10}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://shemspeed.com/stand-with-israel-and-perry-farrell/ |title=Stand with Israel and Perry Farrell |publisher=Shemspeed |date= |accessdate=2017-08-10}}</ref>\n\nAlong with Immersive Artistry and Caesars Entertainment, Perry Farrell announced '''Kind Heaven''' at a press event in Las Vegas in March 2018. {{Citation needed|date=May 2018}}  Scheduled to open at The LINQ Promenade in Las Vegas in 2019, '''Kind Heaven''' is an entertainment attraction that combines technology and storytelling.{{Citation needed|date=May 2018}}\n\n==Discography==\n'''Psi Com'''\n* 1985 [[Psi Com#Psi Com|Psi Com EP]]\n\n'''Jane's Addiction'''\n* 1987 ''[[Jane's Addiction (album)|Jane's Addiction]]''\n* 1988 ''[[Nothing's Shocking]]''\n* 1990 ''[[Ritual de lo habitual]]''\n* 1991 ''[[Live and Rare (Jane's Addiction album)|Live and Rare]]'' (Compilation of B-Sides and the remix of \"Been Caught Stealing\")\n* 1997 ''[[Kettle Whistle (album)|Kettle Whistle]]'' (compilation of live tracks, demos and unreleased material)\n* 2003 ''[[Strays (Jane's Addiction album)|Strays]]''\n* 2006 ''[[Up from the Catacombs - The Best of Jane's Addiction|Up from the Catacombs]]'' (greatest hits album)\n* 2009 ''[[A Cabinet of Curiosities]]'' (box set)\n* 2011 ''[[The Great Escape Artist]]''\n\n'''Porno for Pyros'''\n* 1993 ''[[Porno for Pyros (album)|Porno for Pyros]]''\n* 1996 ''[[Good God's Urge]]''\n\n'''Solo'''\n* 1999 ''[[Rev (Perry Farrell album)|Rev]]'' (Compilation)\n* 2001 ''[[Song Yet to Be Sung]]''\n* 2019 ''[[Kind Heaven]]''<ref>{{cite web |last1=Blais-Billie |first1=Braudie |title=Perry Farrell Announces First Solo Album in 18 Years, Shares New Song: Listen |url=https://pitchfork.com/news/perry-farrell-announces-first-solo-album-in-18-years-shares-new-song-listen/ |website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]] |accessdate=March 29, 2019 |date=March 29, 2019}}</ref>\n\n'''Satellite Party'''\n* 2007 ''[[Ultra Payloaded]]''\n\n'''Miscellaneous musical appearances and collaborations'''\n*Sampled on the track \"Ringfinger\" on the [[Nine Inch Nails]] album ''[[Pretty Hate Machine]]'' (1989).\n*Featured on the track \"[[Ripple (song)|Ripple]]\" on a tribute/environmental benefit to the [[Grateful Dead]] called ''[[Deadicated]]'' (1991).\n*Contributed vocals to the song \"Hot Lava\" on ''[[Chef Aid: The South Park Album]]'' (1998).\n*Contributed vocals to the song \"Children of Night\" along with [[Exene Cervenka]] for [[the Doors]] tribute album ''[[Stoned Immaculate: The Music of the Doors]]'' (2000).\n*Featured on the track \"King Z\" on [[Mad Professor]]'s \"best of\" album ''[[Method to the Madness]]'' (2005).\n*Featured on the track \"Time of your Life\" on [[Paul Oakenfold]]'s album ''[[Bunkka]]'' (2002).\n*Contributed vocals to the song \"The Patience Bossa\" along with [[Debbie Harry]] for the compilation album ''[[A World of Happiness]]'' (2004).\n*Featured on the track \"Revolution Solution\" on [[Thievery Corporation]]'s album ''[[The Cosmic Game]]'' (2005).\n*Featured on the track \"Dogstar\" on [[Hybrid (producers)|Hybrid]]'s album ''[[I Choose Noise]]'' (2006).\n*Featured on the track \"Shake My Shit\" on [[The Nightwatchman]]'s album ''[[The Fabled City]]'' (2008).\n*Contributed the song \"Go All the Way (Into the Twilight)\" to the ''Twilight'' [[Twilight (soundtrack)|Soundtrack]] (2008).\n*Contributed the song \"Nasty Little Perv\" to ''[[NCIS: The Official TV Soundtrack]]'' (2009).\n*Contributed the song \"New Moon\" to the compilation album ''A World of Happiness'' (2009 re-release only).\n*Contributed vocals to the song \"[[Killing Time (Infected Mushroom EP)|Killing Time]]\" on [[Infected Mushroom]]'s album ''[[Legend of the Black Shawarma]]'' (2009).\n*Featured on the track \"Honey If You Love Him\" on [[Erasure]] singer [[Andy Bell (singer)|Andy Bell]]'s album ''[[Non-Stop (Andy Bell album)|Non-Stop]]'' (2010).\n\n==References==\n\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Perry Farrell}}\n*[http://www.perryfarrell.com perryfarrell.com \u2013 Official Artist Site]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20161006215619/http://perry-farrell.net/ perry-farrell.net]\n*[http://arquivo.pt/wayback/20090628210601/http://www.virginrecords.com/perry/ Perry on Virgin Records]\n*[http://www.links.net/dox/muzik/rok/janes/perry/ Justin's Jane's Addiction: Perry Farrell]\n*{{IMDb name|id=0268309}}\n*[http://www.vh1.com/artists/az/farrell_perry/artist.jhtml Perry Farrell \u2013 VH1]\n*[http://synthesisradio.net/2007/05/01/perry-farrell-may-2007/ April 2007 Podcast Interview with Perry Farrell at SynthesisRadio.net]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20071015064454/http://www.prefixmag.com/blog/video-perry-farrell-solutionist-movement/5418 Videos from a May 2007 Press Conference with Perry Farrell]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20080409033455/http://www.kevchino.com/interview/perry-farrell/54 Interview] on kevchino.com\n\n{{Perry Farrell}}\n{{Jane's Addiction}}\n{{Porno for Pyros}}\n{{Satellite Party}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Farrell, Perry}}\n[[Category:1959 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American male singers]]\n[[Category:American rock singers]]\n[[Category:American tenors]]\n[[Category:Music festival founders]]\n[[Category:Jewish American musicians]]\n[[Category:Jewish heavy metal musicians]]\n[[Category:Singers from New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Jane's Addiction members]]\n[[Category:Porno for Pyros members]]\n[[Category:People from Queens, New York]]\n[[Category:People from Bayside, Queens]]\n[[Category:People from Woodmere, New York]]\n[[Category:Alternative metal musicians]]\n[[Category:Satellite Party members]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American singer-songwriter and musician|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=July 2014}}\n{{Infobox musical artist  <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject Musicians -->\n| name                = Perry Farrell\n| image               = Perry Farrell performing with Jane's Addiction at BFD 2012.jpg\n| caption             = Perry Farrell performing with Jane's Addiction at BFD 2012\n| image_size          = 220px\n| background          = solo_singer\n| birth_name          = Peretz Bernstein\n| alias               = DJ Peretz\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1959|3|29}}\n| birth_place         = [[Queens]], [[New York City]], [[New York (state)|New York]], U.S.\n| instrument          = {{flatlist|\n*[[Vocals]]\n*[[turntables]]\n}}<!-- Only primary instruments. -->\n| genre               = {{flatlist|\n*[[Alternative rock]]<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.allmusic.com/artist/perry-farrell-mn0000312991/biography | title=Perry Farrell biography | publisher=[[Allmusic]] | accessdate=November 8, 2015 | author=Prato, Greg}}</ref>\n*[[hard rock]]<ref>{{cite web | url=http://exclaim.ca/music/article/perry_farrell-rev | title=Perry Farrell - Rev | work=[[Exclaim!]] | date=December 1, 1999 | accessdate=December 19, 2015 | author=Gramlich, Chris}}</ref>\n*[[electronica]]<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/song-yet-to-be-sung-mw0000004554 | title=Perry Farrell - Song Yet to Be Sung | publisher=[[Allmusic]] | accessdate=November 8, 2015 | author=[[Stephen Thomas Erlewine|Erlewine, Stephen Thomas]]}}</ref>\n}}\n| occupation          = {{flatlist|\n*Singer-songwriter\n*musician\n*DJ\n}}\n| years_active        = 1981\u2013present\n| label               = {{flatlist|\n*[[Warner Bros. Records|Warner Bros.]]\n*[[EMI]]/[[Capitol Records|Capitol]]\n*[[Columbia Records|Columbia]]\n}}\n| associated_acts     = {{flatlist|\n*[[Jane's Addiction]]\n*[[Porno for Pyros]]\n*[[Psi Com]]\n*[[Satellite Party]]\n*PerryEtty vs [[Chris Cox (DJ)|Chris Cox]]\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Perry Farrell''' (born '''Peretz Bernstein'''; March 29, 1959)<ref name=biography/><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.papermag.com/kabalapalooza-perry-farrell-1425145754.html | title=Kabalapalooza: Perry Farrell | work=[[Paper (magazine)|Paper]] | date=February 1, 2001 | accessdate=November 8, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://nypost.com/2011/10/16/surf-drugs-and-rock-n-roll/ | title=Surf, drugs and rock \u2019n\u2019 roll | work=[[New York Post]] | date=October 16, 2011 | accessdate=November 8, 2015 | author=Aquilante, Dan}}</ref> is an American singer-songwriter and musician, best known as the frontman for the [[alternative rock]] band [[Jane's Addiction]]. Farrell created the touring festival [[Lollapalooza]] as a farewell tour for Jane's Addiction in 1991; it has since evolved into an annual destination festival. Farrell continues to produce Lollapalooza with partners William Morris Agency and C3 Presents. Farrell has also led the alternative rock groups [[Porno for Pyros]] and [[Satellite Party]]. He is the only person who has performed at all twelve [[Coachella Valley Music and Arts Festival]]s to date, having appeared under five different names (Perry Farrell, Jane's Addiction, DJ Peretz, Satellite Party, and with [[Hybrid (Welsh band)|Hybrid]]).\n\n==Biography==\nBorn as Peretz Bernstein in [[Queens]], [[New York City]], [[New York (state)|New York]], he spent his grade-school years in [[Woodmere, New York|Woodmere, Long Island]], and moved to [[North Miami Beach]], [[Florida]], with his [[Jewish]] family during his teens.<ref name=biography>Mullen, Brendan. [https://books.google.com/books?id=RXE0biSWhGIC&pg=PA1&lpg=PA1&dq=Perry+Farrell+woodmere&source=bl&ots=YLqsov-p7W&sig=xmSelAtE7cA0gzjbGznpMFAMOJI&hl=en&ei=MBjMSrfsLYSQsgOrqdCPAQ&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1#v=onepage&q=Perry%20Farrell%20woodmere&f=false Google Books], ''Whores: An Oral Biography of Perry Farrell and Jane's Addiction''. Cambridge: Da Capo, 2005. {{ISBN|0-306-81347-5}}</ref> His father was a jeweler and his mother was an artist who died by suicide when Farrell was three, an event later noted in the Jane's Addiction songs \"Then She Did\" and \"Twisted Tales\". \n\nHis early musical influences included [[The Beatles]], [[The Rolling Stones]], [[Led Zeppelin]], [[Sly & The Family Stone]] and [[James Brown]].<ref name=biography/> Soon after, he discovered [[David Bowie]], [[Iggy Pop]] and [[Lou Reed]]. Following graduation from high school, Farrell moved to California in the early 1980s to live as a surfer.  There, he lived in his car and made money working construction and waiting tables.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.spin.com/2003/07/my-life-music-perry-farrell/|title=My Life in Music: Perry Farrell|publisher=Spin.com|accessdate=2013-07-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kevchino.com/band/perry-farrell/1149|title=Perry Farrell|publisher=Kevchino.com|accessdate=2013-07-13|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141226132825/http://kevchino.com/band/perry-farrell/1149|archivedate=December 26, 2014|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nHe has a son, Yobel, with ex-girlfriend Christine Cagle.<ref>{{cite web|author=Ben Mitchell |url=https://www.theguardian.com/theobserver/2003/aug/03/features.magazine57 |title=The story of Jane's Addiction &#124; From the Observer |publisher=The Guardian |date= |accessdate=2017-08-10}}</ref> In 2002, Farrell married [[Etty Lau Farrell]], a professional dancer and singer who has performed in all the Jane's Addiction shows since the 1997 Relapse tour.  The couple now have two sons together, Hezron Wolfgang and Izzadore Bravo.\n\n==Music career==\n\n===Psi Com (1981\u20131985)===\nHe became the frontman for the [[Post-punk]] band [[Psi Com]] in Los Angeles, and traveled in a larger community of area musicians including the bands [[X (U.S. band)|X]], [[Red Hot Chili Peppers]], [[Fishbone]], and [[The Minutemen (band)|Minutemen]].  Psi Com broke up around 1985 and Farrell met [[Eric Avery]] through mutual friends. The two began jam sessions which would become the initial foundation for Jane's Addiction. It was during this period that Bernstein chose the pseudonym Perry Farrell for himself as a play on the word \"peripheral\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/music/artist/farrell_perry/artist.jhtml|title=Perry Farrell &#124; New Music And Songs|publisher=MTV|date=March 29, 1959|accessdate=2013-07-13}}</ref>\n\n===Jane's Addiction <small>(1985\u20131991, 1997, 2001\u20132004, 2008\u2013present)</small>===\nJane's Addiction made its name in mid-1980s LA by building up a rabid fan base with legendary, high-energy shows in small LA rock clubs. Jane's Addiction, prior to their first break-up, released three albums ''[[Jane's Addiction (album)|Jane's Addiction]]'', ''[[Nothing's Shocking]]'' and ''[[Ritual de lo Habitual]]''. A B-sides album from the ''Ritual'' sessions, titled ''Live and Rare'' was released in Japan. Late in 1991, Jane's Addiction broke up due to internal tensions over differing ideologies mostly centering on drug use, notably Farrell's severe addiction to heroin. Around this time, as mentioned in the SPIN Magazine (1991 Vol. 7 Num. 3) article about their \"Ritual\" tour, a rumor got around that Farrell had contracted HIV. Apparently for amusement, Farrell would tease audiences with \"news\" of his supposed health and would neither confirm nor deny its truth. \nIn 1993 Farrell and his ex-girlfriend Casey Niccoli released a film called ''[[Gift (1993 film)|Gift]]'' that featured Jane's Addiction. Gift was released by [[Warner Brothers]]. In 1997, Jane's Addiction reformed for a brief reunion tour with [[Flea (musician)|Flea]] replacing Avery on bass. The \"Relapse Tour\" was supported with the release of ''[[Kettle Whistle (album)|Kettle Whistle]]'', a rarities album featuring four new songs. {{citation needed|date=February 2014}}\n\nFarrell has sometimes been credited with changing the fortunes of the [[Coachella Valley Music and Arts Festival]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://musicians.about.com/od/musicfestivals/p/coachella.htm|title=Coachella Music Festival \u2013 Coachella \u2013 Profile of Coachella Music Festival|publisher=Musicians.about.com|date=June 22, 2013|accessdate=2013-07-13}}</ref> Following the festival's disastrous first year in 1999, the event was not held in 2000. In 2001, a decision was made to organize the festival again, but just a few months before the festival was set to occur, there was still no headlining group. Farrell, who was friends with the festival's organizers, decided to reunite Jane's Addiction for the 2001 event, which helped draw large crowds and allowed the festival to yield a profit (which was not the case in 1999). This began a Coachella tradition of reuniting at least one major artist each year.\n\nFarrell again toured with Jane's Addiction in 2001 and 2003.  In 2003, Jane's Addiction released an album, ''[[Strays (Jane's Addiction album)|Strays]]''. It quickly became one of their best selling records and was certified gold in the USA and silver in UK.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.riaa.com/goldandplatinumdata.php?table=SEARCH_RESULTS |title=Gold & Platinum Searchable Database \u2013 July 12, 2013 |publisher=RIAA |accessdate=2013-07-13 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070626051113/http://www.riaa.com/goldandplatinumdata.php?table=SEARCH_RESULTS |archivedate=June 26, 2007 |df=mdy-all }}</ref><ref>[http://www.bpi.co.uk/platinum/platinumright.asp?rq=search_plat&r_id=31076] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090218103035/http://www.bpi.co.uk/platinum/platinumright.asp?rq=search_plat&r_id=31076|date=February 18, 2009}}</ref> They toured extensively in North America and Europe, brought back [[Lollapalooza]] for the first time since 1997, as well as performing at the [[Big Day Out]] festivals in Australia and [[New Zealand]]. Internal struggles saw the band split up again in early 2004. A \"best of\" release following the breakup of this incarnation of the band was released in 2006, titled ''[[Up from the Catacombs - The Best of Jane's Addiction|Up from the Catacombs]]''.\n\nThe four original members of Jane's Addiction played their first show together in 17 years at the first United States edition of the NME Awards on April 23, 2008, and played two small shows in Los Angeles during Winter 2008. The band is the first American band to receive the \"God Like Genius\" Award. The reunited Jane's Addiction re-debuted at [[SXSW]] in 2009 and kicked off a summer tour with [[Nine Inch Nails]]. Eric Avery again left the band in late 2009, leaving Farrell, Navarro and Perkins as the remaining members of Jane's Addiction. The band with [[Dave Sitek]] on bass released ''[[The Great Escape Artist]]'' in 2011 and have continued to tour.\n\n===Porno for Pyros (1992\u20131998)===\n\nFollowing the break-up of Jane's Addiction, Farrell formed [[Porno for Pyros]] with former bandmate [[Stephen Perkins]] as well as newcomers [[Peter DiStefano]] on guitar and [[Martyn LeNoble]] on bass. Together they released two albums, ''[[Porno for Pyros (album)|Porno for Pyros]]'' and ''[[Good God's Urge]]''.\n\n===Solo career (1999\u2013present)===\n[[File:PerryFarrell.jpg|thumb|220px|right|Perry Farrell with Jane's Addiction <br />December 3, 2009]]\n\nKicking off his solo career, Farrell released ''[[Rev (Perry Farrell album)|rev]]'' in 1999, a compilation featuring songs from his previous two bands as well as two new solo songs. In 2001, he released his debut solo album, ''[[Song Yet to Be Sung]]'', whose lyrics are inspired by [[Kabballah]].\n\nFarrell has released a number of solo tracks online, all of them recorded with the involvement of wife Etty Lau. Their song \"Go All the Way (Into the Twilight)\" appeared on the ''[[Twilight (2008 film)|Twilight]]'' film soundtrack.<ref>[http://www.theinsider.com/photos/1324248_Twilight_Soundtrack_s_Number_1_And_The_Movie_Isn_t_Out] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081114132423/http://www.theinsider.com/photos/1324248_Twilight_Soundtrack_s_Number_1_And_The_Movie_Isn_t_Out|date=November 14, 2008}}</ref>\n\nIn October 2018, Farrell signed with [[BMG Rights Management]], which will release his upcoming album ''Kind Heaven'' in 2019.<ref name=\"kind\">{{cite web |title=JANE'S ADDICTION Frontman PERRY FARRELL Signs With BMG For New Solo Album, 'Kind Heaven' |url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/janes-addiction-frontman-perry-farrell-signs-with-bmg-for-new-solo-album-kind-heaven |website=[[Blabbermouth.net]] |accessdate=March 29, 2019 |date=October 16, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Satellite Party (2004\u20132008)===\n[[File:PerryFarrellJune07.jpg|thumb|right|200px|Farrell performing at the London Astoria in June 2007]]\nFarrell formed a new band/theatrical entity entitled [[The Satellite Party]]. Satellite Party is a concept album and is the story of a fictional band of musicians called ''The Solutionists'' who are trying to change the world.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.monstersandcritics.com/music/news/article_1255829.php/Farrell_s_Satellite_Party_announces_online_premiere_of_Wish_Upon_A_Dog_Star |title=Farrell's Satellite Party announces online premiere of 'Wish Upon A Dog Star' |publisher=Monsters and Critics |date=February 5, 2007 |accessdate=2013-07-13 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714122803/http://www.monstersandcritics.com/music/news/article_1255829.php/Farrell_s_Satellite_Party_announces_online_premiere_of_Wish_Upon_A_Dog_Star |archivedate=July 14, 2014 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> Farrell conceived the project with his wife [[Etty Lau Farrell]].  Etty sings and plays her part on the record as well as the live stage shows. Satellite Party made its debut in Los Angeles at The Key Club on July 18, 2005, followed by a performance at Lollapalooza 2005, held in [[Grant Park (Chicago)|Grant Park]] in downtown Chicago on July 24, 2005.\n\nTheir debut album, ''[[Ultra Payloaded]]'', was released on May 29, 2007, on [[Columbia Records]], with contributions from artists such as [[John Frusciante]] and [[Flea (musician)|Flea]] of the [[Red Hot Chili Peppers]], electronic dance producers [[Hybrid (Welsh band)|Hybrid]], former [[Red Hot Chili Peppers]]/[[Pearl Jam]] drummer [[Jack Irons]], [[Joy Division]]/[[New Order (band)|New Order]] bassist [[Peter Hook]], and [[Fergie (singer)|Fergie]] of [[The Black Eyed Peas]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Harris |first=Chris |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1501007/flea-contributing-new-farrell-project.jhtml |title=Flea, Frusciante Contributing To Farrell's Next Big Concept \u2013 Music, Celebrity, Artist News |publisher=MTV.com |date=April 29, 2005 |accessdate=2013-07-13}}</ref>\n\nSatellite Party performed at the [[Coachella Valley Music and Arts Festival]] on April 27, 2007. On June 8 they performed at the [[Download Festival]] at Donington, UK.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.downloadfestival.co.uk/history/2007 |title=DOWNLOAD FESTIVAL 2007 &#124; Download Festival 2013 |publisher=Downloadfestival.co.uk |date= |accessdate=2013-07-13}}</ref> On June 29 they performed alongside [[Pearl Jam]], [[Kings of Leon]] and [[Queens of the Stone Age]] at [[Rock Werchter]], Belgium. They performed at Buzz Beach Ball 3 in [[Kansas City, Missouri|Kansas City]], Missouri (a concert sponsored by [[KRBZ]]), and EndFest 16 in [[Seattle, Washington]].\n\n==Lollapalooza==\nIn 1991, prior to Jane's Addiction dissolving, Farrell, Ted Gardener, and Marc Geiger created the [[Lollapalooza]] festival as a farewell tour for Jane's Addiction. From its inception through 1997, and its revival in 2003, the festival toured North America. In 2004, the festival organizers decided to expand the dates to two days per city, but poor ticket sales forced the tour to be canceled.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/life/music/news/2004-06-22-festival-canceled_x.htm |title=Lollapalooza 2004 cancels all dates |publisher=Usatoday.Com |date=June 22, 2004 |accessdate=2013-07-13}}</ref> In 2005, Farrell and the [[William Morris Agency]] partnered up with [[Austin, Texas]]-based company Capital Sports Entertainment (now [[C3 Presents]]) and retooled it as a weekend destination festival in [[Grant Park (Chicago)|Grant Park]], Chicago, Illinois.\n\n===Kidzapalooza===\nIn 2005, music producer [[Tor Hyams]] approached Farrell with the idea of creating a kids' stage with family-friendly fare at [[Lollapalooza]].  Kidzapalooza came to be that year, produced by Hyams and continues to this day with guests like [[Slash (musician)|Slash]], [[Patti Smith]] and [[LeAnn Rimes]] appearing in the lineup of artists.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kidzapalooza.com/about/ |title=Kidzapalooza |publisher=Kidzapalooza |date= |accessdate=2013-07-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.timeoutchicagokids.com/arts-entertainment/movies-music-stage/42415/kidzapalooza-2011 |title=Kidzapalooza 2011 lineup announced |publisher=Time Out Chicago Kids |date=May 10, 2011 |accessdate=2013-07-13}}</ref>\n\n===PurimPalooza 2006===\nIn 2006, Farrell performed at Purimpalooza, which celebrates the Jewish holiday of [[Purim]]. It was a concert for all ages and presented different Jewish musical groups. It took place in [[Ruby Skye]] in San Francisco, and featured bands including Moshav, Chutzpah, and [[Matisyahu]].\n\n==Work outside music==\nFarrell has also made a docudrama titled ''Gift'' released in 1993 which featured various songs by Farrell and included Farrell's then-girlfriend Casey Niccoli. [[Gift (1993 film)|Gift]] was released to VHS home video by Warner Bros but never released to DVD.\n\nHe joined forces with [[Tom Morello]] and his [[Axis of Justice]] tour to raise money for the homeless in Los Angeles and together they both physically removed debris in the [[Ninth Ward]] of New Orleans in the aftermath of Hurricane Katrina to assist local musicians.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thenation.com/article/relentless-activism-tom-morello |title=The Relentless Activism of Tom Morello |first=Z.P. |last=Heller |publisher=The Nation |date=September 15, 2008 |accessdate=2013-07-13}}</ref> They also fund-raised for \"Road Recovery\" a New York non-profit organization which helps young people battling with addiction and other adversities.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.roadrecovery.org |title=Home |publisher=Road Recovery |date= |accessdate=2013-07-13}}</ref>\n\nFarrell is an environmentalist. He met with British prime minister [[Tony Blair]] at [[10 Downing Street]] on January 31, 2007, to discuss global warming. He presented Blair with a CD of the Satellite Party track \"Woman in the Window\".\n\nHe worked with [[Global Cool]] in 2007 to help promote green living.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nme.com/news/perry-farrell/26148 |title=Perry Farrell, Doors drummer launch Global Cool &#124; News |publisher=Nme.Com |date=January 30, 2007 |accessdate=2013-07-13}}</ref>\n\nFarrell has worked to bring music festivals to Israel, including Lollapalooza, and Jane's Addiction itself has performed in Israel.<ref name=\"spin.com\">{{cite web|url=https://www.spin.com/2012/08/perry-farrell-will-bring-lollapalooza-2013-israel/ |title=Perry Farrell Will Bring Lollapalooza 2013 to Israel |publisher=SPIN |date=2012-08-06 |accessdate=2017-08-10}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Billboard |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/1521648/lollapalooza-israel-canceled-were-sorry |title=Lollapalooza Israel Canceled: 'We're Sorry' |publisher=Billboard |date=2013-01-23 |accessdate=2017-08-10}}</ref> However, the Lollapalooza event fell through, with the organizers citing financial concerns and lack of talent willing to perform in Israel. Farrell starred and sang at a \"Stand with Israel\" party held at 7 World Trade Center, just outside [[Ground Zero]] in New York City.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/all_comments?v=sAmQE98wN3Q |title=Perry Farrell at Stand with Israel Event in NYC |publisher=YouTube |date= |accessdate=2017-08-10}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://shemspeed.com/stand-with-israel-and-perry-farrell/ |title=Stand with Israel and Perry Farrell |publisher=Shemspeed |date= |accessdate=2017-08-10}}</ref>\n\nAlong with Immersive Artistry and Caesars Entertainment, Perry Farrell announced '''Kind Heaven''' at a press event in Las Vegas in March 2018. {{Citation needed|date=May 2018}}  Scheduled to open at The LINQ Promenade in Las Vegas in 2019, '''Kind Heaven''' is an entertainment attraction that combines technology and storytelling.{{Citation needed|date=May 2018}}\n\n==Discography==\n'''Psi Com'''\n* 1985 [[Psi Com#Psi Com|Psi Com EP]]\n\n'''Jane's Addiction'''\n* 1987 ''[[Jane's Addiction (album)|Jane's Addiction]]''\n* 1988 ''[[Nothing's Shocking]]''\n* 1990 ''[[Ritual de lo habitual]]''\n* 1991 ''[[Live and Rare (Jane's Addiction album)|Live and Rare]]'' (Compilation of B-Sides and the remix of \"Been Caught Stealing\")\n* 1997 ''[[Kettle Whistle (album)|Kettle Whistle]]'' (compilation of live tracks, demos and unreleased material)\n* 2003 ''[[Strays (Jane's Addiction album)|Strays]]''\n* 2006 ''[[Up from the Catacombs - The Best of Jane's Addiction|Up from the Catacombs]]'' (greatest hits album)\n* 2009 ''[[A Cabinet of Curiosities]]'' (box set)\n* 2011 ''[[The Great Escape Artist]]''\n\n'''Porno for Pyros'''\n* 1993 ''[[Porno for Pyros (album)|Porno for Pyros]]''\n* 1996 ''[[Good God's Urge]]''\n\n'''Solo'''\n* 1999 ''[[Rev (Perry Farrell album)|Rev]]'' (Compilation)\n* 2001 ''[[Song Yet to Be Sung]]''\n* 2019 ''[[Kind Heaven]]''<ref>{{cite web |last1=Blais-Billie |first1=Braudie |title=Perry Farrell Announces First Solo Album in 18 Years, Shares New Song: Listen |url=https://pitchfork.com/news/perry-farrell-announces-first-solo-album-in-18-years-shares-new-song-listen/ |website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]] |accessdate=March 29, 2019 |date=March 29, 2019}}</ref>\n\n'''Satellite Party'''\n* 2007 ''[[Ultra Payloaded]]''\n\n'''Miscellaneous musical appearances and collaborations'''\n*Sampled on the track \"Ringfinger\" on the [[Nine Inch Nails]] album ''[[Pretty Hate Machine]]'' (1989).\n*Featured on the track \"[[Ripple (song)|Ripple]]\" on a tribute/environmental benefit to the [[Grateful Dead]] called ''[[Deadicated]]'' (1991).\n*Contributed vocals to the song \"Hot Lava\" on ''[[Chef Aid: The South Park Album]]'' (1998).\n*Contributed vocals to the song \"Children of Night\" along with [[Exene Cervenka]] for [[the Doors]] tribute album ''[[Stoned Immaculate: The Music of the Doors]]'' (2000).\n*Featured on the track \"King Z\" on [[Mad Professor]]'s \"best of\" album ''[[Method to the Madness]]'' (2005).\n*Featured on the track \"Time of your Life\" on [[Paul Oakenfold]]'s album ''[[Bunkka]]'' (2002).\n*Contributed vocals to the song \"The Patience Bossa\" along with [[Debbie Harry]] for the compilation album ''[[A World of Happiness]]'' (2004).\n*Featured on the track \"Revolution Solution\" on [[Thievery Corporation]]'s album ''[[The Cosmic Game]]'' (2005).\n*Featured on the track \"Dogstar\" on [[Hybrid (producers)|Hybrid]]'s album ''[[I Choose Noise]]'' (2006).\n*Featured on the track \"Shake My Shit\" on [[The Nightwatchman]]'s album ''[[The Fabled City]]'' (2008).\n*Contributed the song \"Go All the Way (Into the Twilight)\" to the ''Twilight'' [[Twilight (soundtrack)|Soundtrack]] (2008).\n*Contributed the song \"Nasty Little Perv\" to ''[[NCIS: The Official TV Soundtrack]]'' (2009).\n*Contributed the song \"New Moon\" to the compilation album ''A World of Happiness'' (2009 re-release only).\n*Contributed vocals to the song \"[[Killing Time (Infected Mushroom EP)|Killing Time]]\" on [[Infected Mushroom]]'s album ''[[Legend of the Black Shawarma]]'' (2009).\n*Featured on the track \"Honey If You Love Him\" on [[Erasure]] singer [[Andy Bell (singer)|Andy Bell]]'s album ''[[Non-Stop (Andy Bell album)|Non-Stop]]'' (2010).\n\n==References==\n\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Perry Farrell}}\n*[http://www.perryfarrell.com perryfarrell.com \u2013 Official Artist Site]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20161006215619/http://perry-farrell.net/ perry-farrell.net]\n*[http://arquivo.pt/wayback/20090628210601/http://www.virginrecords.com/perry/ Perry on Virgin Records]\n*[http://www.links.net/dox/muzik/rok/janes/perry/ Justin's Jane's Addiction: Perry Farrell]\n*{{IMDb name|id=0268309}}\n*[http://