ets/gso2.pdf |title=Archived copy |access-date=2014-01-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140201213223/http://www.schsl.org/2011%20Brackets/gso2.pdf |archive-date=2014-02-01 |url-status=dead }}</ref> \n*Softball\n*Swimming (men's): 2004, 2010, 2011, 2014, 2015 AAA-AA-A State runners-up,<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.schsl.org/2004%20brackets/sw%20aaa%20b%20team.htm |title=Archived copy |access-date=2014-01-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140201213231/http://www.schsl.org/2004%20brackets/sw%20aaa%20b%20team.htm |archive-date=2014-02-01 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.schsl.org/2011%20Brackets/SW3finalteam.pdf |title=Archived copy |access-date=2012-01-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111110052748/http://www.schsl.org/2011%20Brackets/SW3finalteam.pdf |archive-date=2011-11-10 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.schsl.org/2010%20Brackets/sw3finalteam.pdf |title=Archived copy |access-date=2012-01-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140201213234/http://www.schsl.org/2010%20Brackets/sw3finalteam.pdf |archive-date=2014-02-01 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref name=\"2015SCHSL\">http://sportstiming.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/2015-SCHSL-AAA-Championships-Final-Results.pdf</ref> 2012, 2013 AAA-AA-A State Champions<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.schsl.org/2012Brackets/sw3team.pdf |title=Archived copy |access-date=2012-10-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130706000154/http://www.schsl.org/2012Brackets/sw3team.pdf |archive-date=2013-07-06 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref name=\"sw3final\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.schsl.org/2013brackets/sw3final.pdf |title=Archived copy |access-date=2013-10-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131124130644/http://www.schsl.org/2013brackets/sw3final.pdf |archive-date=2013-11-24 |url-status=dead }}</ref> \n*Swimming (women's): 2013 AAA-AA-A State runners-up<ref name=\"sw3final\"/> 2014 AAA-AA-A State runners-up, 2015 AAA-AA-A State Champions<ref name=\"2015SCHSL\"/> 2016 AAA-AA-A State Champions{{citation needed|date=April 2019}}\n*Tennis (men's): 2016 AA State Champions<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.schsl.org/2015Brackets/bte2-1.pdf |title=Archived copy |access-date=2016-05-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160429005135/http://www.schsl.org/2015Brackets/bte2-1.pdf |archive-date=2016-04-29 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n*Tennis (women's)\n*Track and field (men's)\n*Track and field (women's)\n*Volleyball\n*Wrestling\n\nState Champion teams:\n*Cross country (men's): 2013\n*Cross country (women's): 2014\n*Golf (men's): 2010\n*Sailing: 2011, 2013, 2014\n*Soccer (men's): 2012, 2014, 2015, 2017, 2018\n*Soccer (women's): 2011, 2013, 2014, 2015, 2017, 2018\n*Swimming (men's): 2012, 2013\n*Swimming (women's): 2015, 2016\n*Tennis (men's): 2016\n\n==Clubs==\nAMHS has over 60 student-run clubs, offering a club for nearly every interest.\n\n{{Div col|colwidth=20em|content=\n*A capella (Unaccompanied Minors)\n*Academic Bowl (2012, 2017, 2018, and 2019 Lowcountry Champions)\n*African Awareness\n*Asian Awareness\n*Chess Club\n*Dirty Birds (the AMHS drum group, acting as a unique band for the school)\n* F<sup>2</sup>: Film and Fine Arts Club\n*[[Fellowship of Christian Athletes]] (FCA)\n*Gay-Straight Alliance (GSA)\n* High School Musical Club\n*Investment Club\n*Junior Intermezzo\n*[[Key Club]]\n*Movie Mania Club\n*[[Mu Alpha Theta]] (math)\n*National French Honor Society\n*National Spanish Honor Society\n*Physics Club\n*[[Science Olympiad]] (2015, 2019 [[South Carolina Science Olympiad|State Champions]])\n*Speech and Debate Team\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.publicschoolreview.com/school_ov/school_id/71973 School profile]\n*[http://amhs.ccsdschools.com AMHS homepage]\n{{North Charleston, South Carolina}}\n{{Education in Charleston County, South Carolina}}\n[[Category:Public high schools in South Carolina]]\n[[Category:Magnet schools in South Carolina]]\n[[Category:Education in North Charleston, South Carolina]]\n[[Category:Schools in Charleston County, South Carolina]]\n[[Category:1988 establishments in North Carolina]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1988]]\n", "name_user": "2606:a000:1310:448c:e5b8:706f:d1d3:ed43", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(more accurate info)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Academic_Magnet_High_School"}
{"title_page": "McClain (band)", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2014}}\n{{Infobox musical artist|<!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject Musicians -->\n| name             = McClain\n| image            = McCLAIN band 2011 cropped.jpg\n| landscape        = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank -->\n| alt              = \n| caption          = McClain in 2011, from left to right: <br />Sierra McClain, [[China Anne McClain]], and Lauryn McClain\n| origin           = [[Atlanta, Georgia]], United States\n| Background       = group_or_band\n| alias            = {{flat list|\n* 3McClainGirls\n* McClain Sisters}}\n| genre            = {{flat list|\n* [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]\n* [[Pop music|pop]]}}\n| years_active     = 2005\u20132016 (on hiatus)\n| label            = [[Hollywood Records|Hollywood Records]] {{small|(2011\u201313)}}\n| website          = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} -->\n| current_members  = * [[China Anne McClain]]\n* Sierra McClain\n* Lauryn McClain\n}}\n'''McClain''' (formerly '''3McClainGirls''' and '''McClain Sisters''') is an American [[girl group]] that was formed in [[Atlanta, Georgia]] in 2004. The group consists of sisters [[China Anne McClain]], Sierra McClain, and Lauryn McClain. They signed with [[Hollywood Records]] in 2011 and released their debut single \"[[Go (McClain Sisters song)|Go]]\" in 2012. In 2013, the group left the record label. Their most recent single \"Feelin' Like\" was released in 2016. The group is now on hiatus and the sisters are pursuing their acting careers. \n\n== Early life ==\nSierra Aylina McClain was born on March 16, 1994<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/name/nm2057826/|title=Sierra Aylina McClain|website=IMDb|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>, Lauryn Alisa McClain was born on January 9, 1997<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/name/nm2055160/|title=Lauryn Alisa McClain|website=IMDb|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>, and China Anne McClain was born on August 25, 1998<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/name/nm1942207/|title=China Anne McClain|website=IMDb|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>. All three sisters were born and raised in [[Atlanta, Georgia]]. Sierra, Lauryn, and China grew up watching [[Disney]] films and musical classics, and come from an artistic and musical family<ref name=\"filmb\">{{cite web|url=http://www.filmbug.com/db/346128|title=Sierra, Lauryn & China Anne McClain|date=March 22, 2012|publisher=Filmbug.com}}</ref> Their father, Michael McClain, is a music producer who produced [[Solange Knowles]]' debut album. Their mother, Shontell McClain, is a songwriter and former screenwriter.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/name/nm2718277/|title=Shontell McClain|website=IMDb|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref> The sisters also have a little brother, Gabriel McClain, who was born on April 17, 2001<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/name/nm2532716/|title=Gabriel McClain|website=IMDb|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>.\n\nIn 2004, the sisters became interested in music when they watched their father write and produce songs. Soon after, the girls began to write songs, choreograph and dance.<ref name=\"lions\">{{cite web|url=http://www.lionsgatepublicity.com/epk/daddyslittlegirls/docs/pro_notes.doc|title=McClain notes on Lionsgate|date=March 22, 2012|publisher=lionsgatepublicity.com|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100206114300/http://lionsgatepublicity.com/epk/daddyslittlegirls/docs/pro_notes.doc|archivedate=February 6, 2010|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\n\n=== 2005\u20132011: 3McClainGirls and ''Daddy's Little Girls'' ===\nIn 2005, the sisters were discovered as actresses by a music executive who heard them sing and encouraged director [[Rob Hardy]] to audition China for his 2005 feature film ''[[The Gospel (film)|The Gospel]].'' China was cast as the character Alexis and her sisters were in the supporting cast.<ref name=\"dc\">{{cite web |url=http://disneychannelmedianet.com/web/showpage/showpage.aspx?program_id=900056&type=mcclain |title=Disney Channel Bio \u2013 China Anne McClain |publisher=Disney Channel Medianet |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/63XM5Q2Ie?url=http://disneychannelmedianet.com/web/showpage/showpage.aspx?program_id=900056&type=mcclain |archivedate=November 28, 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref> The sisters became more serious about a musical career and formed the girl group the 3McClainGirls. \n\nThey recorded their first song, \"Silly Games\". The song was produced by their father, Michael McClain, and written by their mother, Shontell McClain.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ovguide.com/3mcclaingirls-9202a8c04000641f8000000006afa58b# |title=3McClainGirls Music |publisher=OV Guide |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/63XM5Q2Ie?url=http://disneychannelmedianet.com/web/showpage/showpage.aspx?program_id=900056&type=mcclain |archivedate=November 28, 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref> In 2006 China joined the main cast of ''[[Tyler Perry's House of Payne]]'' as Jazmine Payne and Sierra made guest appearances. In 2007 the group starred in the film ''[[Daddy's Little Girls]]'' as the James sisters.<ref name=\"lions\" /> In 2008 the group recorded the song \"Daddy's Girls\",<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/daddys-girl-mw0001655815 |title=3mcclaingirls! Daddy's Girl |publisher=Allmusic |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/63XM5Q2Ie?url=http://disneychannelmedianet.com/web/showpage/showpage.aspx?program_id=900056&type=mcclain |archivedate=November 28, 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref> inspired by the movie, and released it exclusively on Myspace.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.myspace.com/mcclainsisters |title=3mcclaingirls Official Myspace |publisher=Myspace |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/63XM5Q2Ie?url=http://disneychannelmedianet.com/web/showpage/showpage.aspx?program_id=900056&type=mcclain |archivedate=November 28, 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref> In 2008 the group began posting videos on Youtube of themselves singing covers of songs and continued making acting appearances in films and on television.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCksYLtnxiIW0UTegpdbseMQ|title=3mcclaingirls|website=YouTube|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n\n=== 2011\u20132013: McClain Sisters, ''A.N.T. Farm'' and Hollywood Records ===\nOn June 14, 2011 the group signed with [[Hollywood Records]].<ref name=\"hollywoodrecords\">{{cite web|url=http://www.blackcelebkids.com/2012/03/13/mcclain-sisters-sign-with-hollywood-records/|title=MCCLAIN SISTERS SIGN WITH HOLLYWOOD RECORDS|publisher=Black Celeb Kids|date=June 14, 2011|access-date=February 9, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130126042852/http://www.blackcelebkids.com/2012/03/13/mcclain-sisters-sign-with-hollywood-records/|archive-date=January 26, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> The sisters originally planned to use the name III as their group name, the number representing the three McClain girls in the group, but that idea was scrapped.<ref name=\":1\" /> They instead changed their group name to the McClain Sisters. That same year China landed her own show on the [[Disney Channel]] called [[A.N.T. Farm]]. On October 11, 2011, the [[A.N.T. Farm (soundtrack)]] was released on which the group had two songs: \"Perfect Mistake\" and \"Electronic Apology\". The group had plans to release their debut album with the record label<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|last=Barnes|first=Brooks|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/05/11/arts/television/tween-stars-wanted-must-be-primed-for-pressure.html|title=Tween Stars Wanted: Must Be Primed for Pressure|date=2011-05-10|work=The New York Times|access-date=2020-04-05|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> but never did. In December the group performed their version of [[Jingle Bell Rock]] at the 2011 [[Disney Parks Christmas Day Parade]].<ref>{{Citation|title=Christmas Parade 2011 McClain Sisters - Celebrity Take with Jake|url=https://video.disney.com/watch/christmas-parade-2011-mcclain-sisters-4bb39f0d70be4a8833003b15|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tigerbeat.com/2011/11/exclusive-bop-and-tiger-beats-photo-shoot-with-china/onerepublic-and-china-anne-mcclain-and-the-mcclain-sisters-perform-for-the-2011-disney-parks-christmas-day-parade/|title=OneRepublic and China Anne McClain and The McClain Sisters Perform for The 2011 Disney Parks Christmas Day Parade {{!}} TigerBeat|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n\nOn March 4, 2012 they were the opening act in [[Houston]] for [[Big Time Rush (group)|Big Time Rush]] on their [[Better with U Tour]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.houstonchronicle.com/news/houston-texas/article/Big-Time-Rush-show-leaves-little-to-like-3381325.php|title=Big Time Rush show leaves little to like|date=2012-03-05|website=HoustonChronicle.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/houston-livestock-show-and-rodeo-officials-announce-star-studded-entertainer-lineup-ticket-sales-information-136945508.html|title=Houston Livestock Show and Rodeo\u2122 Officials Announce Star-studded Entertainer Lineup, Ticket Sales Information|last=Rodeo|first=Houston Livestock Show &|website=www.prnewswire.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref>  \n\nOn March 11, 2012 they performed a new song called \"Rise\" at the [[Mall of America]]. The song was written by the McClain Sisters and produced by father Michael McClain, and was the lead promotional single for the [[Disneynature]] film [[Chimpanzee (film)|''Chimpanzee'']]. The song was released on March 23, 2012. The music video premiered on March 25, 2012 during an episode of ''[[Austin & Ally]]''. It was also a featured song for [[Disney's Friends for Change]]..<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mallofamerica.com/upload/event/pdf/ChinaGuidelinesUPDATE.pdf|title=China Anne McClain & the McClain Sisters Performance and Signing|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> The music video later premiered online on March 26, 2012.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uxVeeqqAyf0|title=McClain Sisters - Rise (Official Video from Disneynature's Chimpanzee)|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> \n\nOn September 11, 2012, their single [[The Great Divide (McClain Sisters song)|The Great Divide]] was released which was featured in the Disney film [[Secret of the Wings]] and on the film's soundtrack [[Disney Fairies: Faith, Trust, and Pixie Dust]]. \n\nOn November 2, 2012, the McClain Sisters premiered their debut single \"[[Go (McClain Sisters song)|Go]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/go-single/id573043137|title=Music \u2013 Go - iTunes United States|publisher=iTunes Store (US). Apple|accessdate=September 26, 2012}}</ref> Lauryn and Sierra guest starred and performed the song, alongside China, on November 23, 2012 during the episode \"[[List of A.N.T. Farm episodes#ep41|chANTs of a lifetime]]\" for ''[[A.N.T. Farm]].'' \n\n=== 2013\u2013present: Leaving Hollywood Records, McClain, and hiatus ===\nIn December of 2013, China announced on Twitter that [[A.N.T. Farm]] would be ending after its third season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/chinamcclain/status/416460834571694080|title=It was GREAT filming ANT Farm but after 3 seasons it's come to an end. I'm excited about my secret projects and keeping you guys happy!|last=China\u2077|date=2013-12-26|website=@chinamcclain|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref> Shortly after this announcement, the McClain Sisters parted ways with [[Hollywood Records]]. After leaving the record label the group changed their name from the McClain Sisters to simply McClain. The group released an official lyric video for their single \"He Loves Me\" on YouTube on December 14, 2013.<ref>{{Citation|last=mcclainsisters|title=He Loves Me- Lyric Video|date=2013-12-14|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Z21wV7XRaqs|accessdate=2016-06-13}}</ref> The song then became available on iTunes on February 20, 2014. Later that year, McClain released a Christmas song called \"The Holiday Song\". \n\nThe last single the sisters released was \"Feelin' Like\" in 2016 and the group now seems to be on hiatus. All three sisters are pursuing their acting careers.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==Personal life==\nThey are [[Christians]] and reside in Los Angeles, California with their family.<ref>{{cite web|title=Biography of China |url=http://chinaanne.net/chinaanne/biography/ |work=chinaanne.net |accessdate=September 26, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121125013234/http://chinaanne.net/chinaanne/biography/ |archivedate=November 25, 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hollowverse.com/china-anne-mcclain/|title=China Anne McClain\u2019s Religion and Political Views|website=hollowverse.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n\n===Singles===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\" border=\"1\"\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:14em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Album\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"[[Disney's Friends for Change#Rise|Rise]]\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/rise-feat.-mcclain-sisters/id509693456|title=Rise \u2013 Single by McClain|publisher=iTunes Store (US). Apple|accessdate=September 26, 2012}}</ref>\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2012\n| rowspan=\"4\" {{n/a|Non-album singles}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"[[Go (McClain Sisters song)|Go]]\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"He Loves Me\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/he-loves-me-single/id827805733|title=He Loves Me \u2013 Single by McClain|publisher=iTunes Store (US). Apple|accessdate=September 26, 2012}}</ref>\n| 2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Feelin' Like\"<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=https://soundcloud.com/officialmcclain/feelin-like-ode-to-aaliyah|title=Feelin' Like \u2013 Single by McClain|publisher=Soundcloud|accessdate=January 14, 2020}}</ref>\n| 2016\n|-\n|}\n\n===Promotional singles===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\" border=\"1\"\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:14em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\"| Album\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Silly Games\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.youngblackstarz.org/2012/04/03/memory-lane-these-girls-had-no-time-for-silly-games/|title=MEMORY LANE: THESE GIRLS HAD NO TIME FOR \"SILLY GAMES\"|work=Young Black Stars|date= |accessdate=May 13, 2010}}</ref><br><span style=\"font-size:85%; <!--font-weight:normal;-->\">(featuring Tiff Mic)</span>\n| 2005\n| rowspan=\"2\" {{n/a|Non-album singles}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Daddy's Girl\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/daddys-girl/id275361079|title=3mcclaingirls! \u2013 Daddy's Girl|work=iTunes|date= |accessdate=May 13, 2010}}</ref>\n| 2008\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"[[Disney Fairies: Faith, Trust And Pixie Dust#The Great Divide|The Great Divide]]\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/great-divide-from-secret-wings/id556729644|title=The Great Divide \u2013 Single by McClain|publisher=iTunes Store (US). Apple|accessdate=September 26, 2012}}</ref>\n| 2012\n| ''[[Disney Fairies: Faith, Trust and Pixie Dust]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"The Holiday Song\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/the-holiday-song-single/id952382814|title=The Holiday Song - Single|publisher=iTunes Store (US). Apple|accessdate=September 26, 2012}}</ref>\n| 2014\n| {{n/a|Non-album single}}\n|-\n|}\n\n===Other appearances===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\" border=\"1\"\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:15em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\"| Album\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Perfect Mistake\"\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2011\n| rowspan=\"2\"| ''[[A.N.T. Farm (soundtrack)|A.N.T. Farm]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Electronic Apology\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Jingle Bell Rock]]\"\n| 2012\n| ''[[Disney Channel Holiday Playlist]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Sharp As a Razor\"\n| 2013\n| ''[[Shake It Up: I Love Dance|Shake It Up: I <3 Dance]]''\n|}\n\n===Music videos===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\" border=\"1\"\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:15em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\"| Year\n! cindy=\"sharp\"| Director\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"[[Rise (McClain Sisters song)|Rise]]\"\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2012\n| Mark Albert\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[The Great Divide (McClain Sisters song)|The Great Divide]] \"\n| {{n/a}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==Concert tours==\n;Opening act:\n* 2012: [[Better with U Tour#Opening act|Better with U Tour]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blackcelebkids.com/2012/03/06/the-mcclain-sisters-take-to-the-stage/|title=THE MCCLAIN SISTERS TAKE TO THE STAGE|work=blackcelebkids.com|date=May 13, 2010|accessdate=May 13, 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120308123351/http://www.blackcelebkids.com/2012/03/06/the-mcclain-sisters-take-to-the-stage/|archive-date=March 8, 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref> {{small|([[Big Time Rush (band)|Big Time Rush]])}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://mcclainsistersmusic.com/ Official website]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Musical groups established in 2011]]\n[[Category:Sibling musical trios]]\n[[Category:American hip hop groups]]\n[[Category:American pop music groups]]\n[[Category:African-American girl groups]]\n[[Category:American contemporary R&B musical groups]]\n[[Category:American girl groups]]\n[[Category:Hollywood Records artists]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2014}}\n{{Infobox musical artist|<!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject Musicians -->\n| name             = McClain\n| image            = McCLAIN band 2011 cropped.jpg\n| landscape        = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank -->\n| alt              = \n| caption          = McClain in 2011, from left to right: <br />Sierra McClain, [[China Anne McClain]], and Lauryn McClain\n| origin           = [[Atlanta, Georgia]], United States\n| Background       = group_or_band\n| alias            = {{flat list|\n* 3McClainGirls\n* McClain Sisters}}\n| genre            = {{flat list|\n* [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]\n* [[Pop music|pop]]}}\n| years_active     = 2005\u20132016 (on hiatus)\n| label            = [[Hollywood Records|Hollywood Records]] {{small|(2011\u201313)}}\n| website          = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} -->\n| current_members  = * [[China Anne McClain]]\n* Sierra McClain\n* Lauryn McClain\n}}\n'''McClain''' (formerly '''3McClainGirls''' and '''McClain Sisters''') is an American [[girl group]] that was formed in [[Atlanta, Georgia]] in 2004. The group consists of sisters [[China Anne McClain]], Sierra McClain, and Lauryn McClain. They signed with [[Hollywood Records]] in 2011 and released their debut single \"[[Go (McClain Sisters song)|Go]]\" in 2012. In 2013, the group left the record label. Their most recent single \"Feelin' Like\" was released in 2016. The group is now on hiatus and the sisters are pursuing their acting careers. \n\n== Early life ==\nSierra Aylina McClain was born on March 16, 1994<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/name/nm2057826/|title=Sierra Aylina McClain|website=IMDb|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>, Lauryn Alisa McClain was born on January 9, 1997<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/name/nm2055160/|title=Lauryn Alisa McClain|website=IMDb|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>, and China Anne McClain was born on August 25, 1998<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/name/nm1942207/|title=China Anne McClain|website=IMDb|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>. All three sisters were born and raised in [[Atlanta, Georgia]]. Sierra, Lauryn, and China grew up watching [[Disney]] films and musical classics, and come from an artistic and musical family<ref name=\"filmb\">{{cite web|url=http://www.filmbug.com/db/346128|title=Sierra, Lauryn & China Anne McClain|date=March 22, 2012|publisher=Filmbug.com}}</ref> Their father, Michael McClain, is a music producer who produced [[Solange Knowles]]' debut album. Their mother, Shontell McClain, is a songwriter and former screenwriter.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/name/nm2718277/|title=Shontell McClain|website=IMDb|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref> The sisters also have a little brother, Gabriel McClain, who was born on April 17, 2001<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/name/nm2532716/|title=Gabriel McClain|website=IMDb|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>.\n\nIn 2004, the sisters became interested in music when they watched their father write and produce songs. Soon after, the girls began to write songs, choreograph and dance.<ref name=\"lions\">{{cite web|url=http://www.lionsgatepublicity.com/epk/daddyslittlegirls/docs/pro_notes.doc|title=McClain notes on Lionsgate|date=March 22, 2012|publisher=lionsgatepublicity.com|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100206114300/http://lionsgatepublicity.com/epk/daddyslittlegirls/docs/pro_notes.doc|archivedate=February 6, 2010|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\n\n=== 2005\u20132011: 3McClainGirls and ''Daddy's Little Girls'' ===\nIn 2005, the sisters were discovered as actresses by a music executive who heard them sing and encouraged director [[Rob Hardy]] to audition China for his 2005 feature film ''[[The Gospel (film)|The Gospel]].'' China was cast as the character Alexis and her sisters were in the supporting cast.<ref name=\"dc\">{{cite web |url=http://disneychannelmedianet.com/web/showpage/showpage.aspx?program_id=900056&type=mcclain |title=Disney Channel Bio \u2013 China Anne McClain |publisher=Disney Channel Medianet |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/63XM5Q2Ie?url=http://disneychannelmedianet.com/web/showpage/showpage.aspx?program_id=900056&type=mcclain |archivedate=November 28, 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref> The sisters became more serious about a musical career and formed the girl group the 3McClainGirls. \n\nThey recorded their first song, \"Silly Games\". The song was produced by their father, Michael McClain, and written by their mother, Shontell McClain.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ovguide.com/3mcclaingirls-9202a8c04000641f8000000006afa58b# |title=3McClainGirls Music |publisher=OV Guide |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/63XM5Q2Ie?url=http://disneychannelmedianet.com/web/showpage/showpage.aspx?program_id=900056&type=mcclain |archivedate=November 28, 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref> In 2006 China joined the main cast of ''[[Tyler Perry's House of Payne]]'' as Jazmine Payne and Sierra made guest appearances. In 2007 the group starred in the film ''[[Daddy's Little Girls]]'' as the James sisters.<ref name=\"lions\" /> In 2008 the group recorded the song \"Daddy's Girls\",<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/daddys-girl-mw0001655815 |title=3mcclaingirls! Daddy's Girl |publisher=Allmusic |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/63XM5Q2Ie?url=http://disneychannelmedianet.com/web/showpage/showpage.aspx?program_id=900056&type=mcclain |archivedate=November 28, 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref> inspired by the movie, and released it exclusively on Myspace.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.myspace.com/mcclainsisters |title=3mcclaingirls Official Myspace |publisher=Myspace |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/63XM5Q2Ie?url=http://disneychannelmedianet.com/web/showpage/showpage.aspx?program_id=900056&type=mcclain |archivedate=November 28, 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref> In 2008 the group began posting videos on Youtube of themselves singing covers of songs and continued making acting appearances in films and on television.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCksYLtnxiIW0UTegpdbseMQ|title=3mcclaingirls|website=YouTube|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n\n=== 2011\u20132013: McClain Sisters, ''A.N.T. Farm'' and Hollywood Records ===\nOn June 14, 2011 the group signed with [[Hollywood Records]].<ref name=\"hollywoodrecords\">{{cite web|url=http://www.blackcelebkids.com/2012/03/13/mcclain-sisters-sign-with-hollywood-records/|title=MCCLAIN SISTERS SIGN WITH HOLLYWOOD RECORDS|publisher=Black Celeb Kids|date=June 14, 2011|access-date=February 9, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130126042852/http://www.blackcelebkids.com/2012/03/13/mcclain-sisters-sign-with-hollywood-records/|archive-date=January 26, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> The sisters originally planned to use the name III as their group name, the number representing the three McClain girls in the group, but that idea was scrapped.<ref name=\":1\" /> They instead changed their group name to the McClain Sisters. That same year China landed her own show on the [[Disney Channel]] called [[A.N.T. Farm]]. On October 11, 2011, the [[A.N.T. Farm (soundtrack)]] was released on which the group had two songs: \"Perfect Mistake\" and \"Electronic Apology\". The group had plans to release their debut album with the record label<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|last=Barnes|first=Brooks|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/05/11/arts/television/tween-stars-wanted-must-be-primed-for-pressure.html|title=Tween Stars Wanted: Must Be Primed for Pressure|date=2011-05-10|work=The New York Times|access-date=2020-04-05|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> but never did. In December the group performed their version of [[Jingle Bell Rock]] at the 2011 [[Disney Parks Christmas Day Parade]].<ref>{{Citation|title=Christmas Parade 2011 McClain Sisters - Celebrity Take with Jake|url=https://video.disney.com/watch/christmas-parade-2011-mcclain-sisters-4bb39f0d70be4a8833003b15|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tigerbeat.com/2011/11/exclusive-bop-and-tiger-beats-photo-shoot-with-china/onerepublic-and-china-anne-mcclain-and-the-mcclain-sisters-perform-for-the-2011-disney-parks-christmas-day-parade/|title=OneRepublic and China Anne McClain and The McClain Sisters Perform for The 2011 Disney Parks Christmas Day Parade {{!}} TigerBeat|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n\nOn March 4, 2012 they were the opening act in [[Houston]] for [[Big Time Rush (group)|Big Time Rush]] on their [[Better with U Tour]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.houstonchronicle.com/news/houston-texas/article/Big-Time-Rush-show-leaves-little-to-like-3381325.php|title=Big Time Rush show leaves little to like|date=2012-03-05|website=HoustonChronicle.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/houston-livestock-show-and-rodeo-officials-announce-star-studded-entertainer-lineup-ticket-sales-information-136945508.html|title=Houston Livestock Show and Rodeo\u2122 Officials Announce Star-studded Entertainer Lineup, Ticket Sales Information|last=Rodeo|first=Houston Livestock Show &|website=www.prnewswire.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref>  \n\nOn March 11, 2012 they performed a new song called \"Rise\" at the [[Mall of America]]. The song was written by the McClain Sisters and produced by father Michael McClain, and was the lead promotional single for the [[Disneynature]] film [[Chimpanzee (film)|''Chimpanzee'']]. The song was released on March 23, 2012. The music video premiered on March 25, 2012 during an episode of ''[[Austin & Ally]]''. It was also a featured song for [[Disney's Friends for Change]]..<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mallofamerica.com/upload/event/pdf/ChinaGuidelinesUPDATE.pdf|title=China Anne McClain & the McClain Sisters Performance and Signing|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> The music video later premiered online on March 26, 2012.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uxVeeqqAyf0|title=McClain Sisters - Rise (Official Video from Disneynature's Chimpanzee)|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> \n\nOn September 11, 2012, their single [[The Great Divide (McClain Sisters song)|The Great Divide]] was released which was featured in the Disney film [[Secret of the Wings]] and on the film's soundtrack [[Disney Fairies: Faith, Trust, and Pixie Dust]]. \n\nOn November 2, 2012, the McClain Sisters premiered their debut single \"[[Go (McClain Sisters song)|Go]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/go-single/id573043137|title=Music \u2013 Go - iTunes United States|publisher=iTunes Store (US). Apple|accessdate=September 26, 2012}}</ref> Lauryn and Sierra guest starred and performed the song, alongside China, on November 23, 2012 during the episode \"[[List of A.N.T. Farm episodes#ep41|chANTs of a lifetime]]\" for ''[[A.N.T. Farm]].'' \n\n=== 2013\u2013present: Leaving Hollywood Records, McClain, and hiatus ===\nIn December of 2013, China announced on Twitter that [[A.N.T. Farm]] would be ending after its third season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/chinamcclain/status/416460834571694080|title=It was GREAT filming ANT Farm but after 3 seasons it's come to an end. I'm excited about my secret projects and keeping you guys happy!|last=China\u2077|date=2013-12-26|website=@chinamcclain|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref> Shortly after this announcement, the McClain Sisters parted ways with [[Hollywood Records]]. After leaving the record label the group changed their name from the McClain Sisters to simply McClain. The group released an official lyric video for their single \"He Loves Me\" on YouTube on December 14, 2013.<ref>{{Citation|last=mcclainsisters|title=He Loves Me- Lyric Video|date=2013-12-14|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Z21wV7XRaqs|accessdate=2016-06-13}}</ref> The song then became available on iTunes on February 20, 2014. Later that year, McClain released a Christmas song called \"The Holiday Song\". \n\nThe last single the sisters released was \"Feelin' Like\" in 2016 and the group now seems to be on hiatus. All three sisters are pursuing their acting careers.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==Personal life==\nThey are [[Christians]] and reside in Los Angeles, California with their family.<ref>{{cite web|title=Biography of China |url=http://chinaanne.net/chinaanne/biography/ |work=chinaanne.net |accessdate=September 26, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121125013234/http://chinaanne.net/chinaanne/biography/ |archivedate=November 25, 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hollowverse.com/china-anne-mcclain/|title=China Anne McClain\u2019s Religion and Political Views|website=hollowverse.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n\n===Singles===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\" border=\"1\"\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:14em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Album\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"[[Disney's Friends for Change#Rise|Rise]]\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/rise-feat.-mcclain-sisters/id509693456|title=Rise \u2013 Single by McClain|publisher=iTunes Store (US). Apple|accessdate=September 26, 2012}}</ref>\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2012\n| rowspan=\"4\" {{n/a|Non-album singles}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"[[Go (McClain Sisters song)|Go]]\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"He Loves Me\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/he-loves-me-single/id827805733|title=He Loves Me \u2013 Single by McClain|publisher=iTunes Store (US). Apple|accessdate=September 26, 2012}}</ref>\n| 2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Feelin' Like\"<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=https://soundcloud.com/officialmcclain/feelin-like-ode-to-aaliyah|title=Feelin' Like \u2013 Single by McClain|publisher=Soundcloud|accessdate=January 14, 2020}}</ref>\n| 2016\n|-\n|}\n\n===Promotional singles===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\" border=\"1\"\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:14em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\"| Album\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Silly Games\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.youngblackstarz.org/2012/04/03/memory-lane-these-girls-had-no-time-for-silly-games/|title=MEMORY LANE: THESE GIRLS HAD NO TIME FOR \"SILLY GAMES\"|work=Young Black S